WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.875
[upbeat music]

00:00:17.208 --> 00:00:19.041
[indistinct kids' shouts and laughter]

00:00:25.250 --> 00:00:27.916
GRADUATION CEREMONY

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:29.375
A photo? Go ahead.

00:00:31.125 --> 00:00:32.750
One, two…

00:00:32.833 --> 00:00:34.833
Hello.

00:00:34.916 --> 00:00:36.291
One, two…

00:00:36.875 --> 00:00:40.500
[indistinct chatter]

00:00:55.583 --> 00:00:57.291
[woman] There he is!

00:00:58.500 --> 00:00:59.500
[man] Mom!

00:01:00.250 --> 00:01:01.500
[chuckles]

00:01:02.500 --> 00:01:07.083
Congrats, dear.
My son officially has a degree.

00:01:07.166 --> 00:01:08.708
Thanks, Mom.

00:01:09.083 --> 00:01:09.916
Dad.

00:01:11.125 --> 00:01:12.083
[sighs in relief]

00:01:12.166 --> 00:01:14.375
I'm so proud of you, son.

00:01:15.333 --> 00:01:16.416
[chuckles] You're amazing.

00:01:16.500 --> 00:01:19.375
Thank God you graduated
in eight semesters.

00:01:19.458 --> 00:01:21.125
Any longer, and I'd be broke.

00:01:21.208 --> 00:01:23.291
[laughing]

00:01:23.375 --> 00:01:25.375
Better get a job soon.

00:01:25.458 --> 00:01:26.958
Try to get into the civil service.

00:01:27.041 --> 00:01:28.041
[whines] Dear…

00:01:28.125 --> 00:01:31.291
Civil servants get pension benefits.

00:01:31.375 --> 00:01:32.416
Amen.

00:01:32.500 --> 00:01:34.125
-Boo!
-Allahu Akbar!

00:01:34.208 --> 00:01:36.166
Rifa.

00:01:36.250 --> 00:01:37.250
I graduated!

00:01:37.333 --> 00:01:39.875
-Congratulations.
-Congratulations.

00:01:39.958 --> 00:01:42.875
-Hello.
-Hi, Fatimah. How are you?

00:01:42.958 --> 00:01:44.250
-I'm doing great.
-Hello, Aunty.

00:01:44.333 --> 00:01:45.458
Fadly, congrats.

00:01:45.541 --> 00:01:48.625
-How are you, sir?
-Congratulations.

00:01:48.708 --> 00:01:50.916
[laughing]

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:52.208
Hey.

00:01:52.291 --> 00:01:54.458
You're more stunning than ever.

00:01:54.541 --> 00:01:56.833
Oh, please.

00:01:57.916 --> 00:01:59.375
-[Fatimah] Right?
-[chuckles]

00:02:02.250 --> 00:02:04.166
Why can't we be like them?

00:02:05.416 --> 00:02:08.875
You're looking good today.

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:12.125
[Rifa] A picture?

00:02:12.208 --> 00:02:13.083
Let's do it.

00:02:15.291 --> 00:02:16.500
[camera clicks]

00:02:20.333 --> 00:02:21.583
[soft hum]

00:02:24.500 --> 00:02:25.750
[sighs in relief]

00:02:27.791 --> 00:02:30.333
So you're pursuing your master's in Jogja?

00:02:32.750 --> 00:02:34.375
Maybe. It depends.

00:02:35.291 --> 00:02:36.416
On what?

00:02:40.750 --> 00:02:42.625
Here, you can keep it.

00:02:42.708 --> 00:02:44.791
In case you start missing me.

00:02:44.875 --> 00:02:46.708
You're so full of yourself.

00:02:46.791 --> 00:02:49.541
-Who would even miss you?
-You will.

00:02:49.625 --> 00:02:51.666
Rifa.

00:02:53.083 --> 00:02:54.291
Shall we head home?

00:02:54.375 --> 00:02:55.541
-Okay.
-All right.

00:02:56.666 --> 00:02:58.291
Fadly.

00:02:58.375 --> 00:03:01.916
Now that you've graduated, what's next?

00:03:02.458 --> 00:03:05.166
I'm going to focus on getting a job.

00:03:05.250 --> 00:03:06.375
Oh.

00:03:06.458 --> 00:03:11.000
I pray that you secure a job fast.

00:03:11.083 --> 00:03:12.083
Amen. [chuckles]

00:03:12.166 --> 00:03:13.125
Amen.

00:03:13.208 --> 00:03:15.250
Take care, Aunty, Uncle.

00:03:15.333 --> 00:03:17.583
-Same goes for you.
-I will.

00:03:17.666 --> 00:03:20.583
Sir, ma'am. We're leaving first.

00:03:20.666 --> 00:03:26.375
-Until next time. Take care.
-Yes, we will.

00:03:26.458 --> 00:03:28.041
[laughing]

00:03:29.083 --> 00:03:30.416
See you.

00:03:30.500 --> 00:03:32.833
-Bye, Aunty, Uncle.
-Bye.

00:03:32.916 --> 00:03:35.458
-[Rifa's mom] Let's go, honey.
-[Fadly] Bye.

00:03:35.541 --> 00:03:38.500
[bright music]

00:03:41.583 --> 00:03:47.208
BASED ON TRUE STORY

00:03:47.750 --> 00:03:49.333
-Come on, Mom.
-Coming.

00:03:50.583 --> 00:03:51.541
I'm hungry.

00:03:51.625 --> 00:03:53.166
Really? I've cooked for you.

00:03:53.250 --> 00:03:54.750
-[chuckles]
-We'll eat later.

00:03:54.833 --> 00:03:56.666
Bismillahirrahmanirrahim.

00:03:56.750 --> 00:03:57.750
Careful.

00:03:57.833 --> 00:04:00.000
-Thanks, son.
-No problem, Mom.

00:04:10.958 --> 00:04:12.916
-Come on, dear.
-Coming.

00:04:15.208 --> 00:04:17.416
[Fatimah] How are you and Rifa?
Are you two dating yet?

00:04:17.500 --> 00:04:19.083
[Fadly] We're just friends, Mom.

00:04:19.166 --> 00:04:22.291
[Mustafa] Someone else
might beat you to it.

00:04:22.375 --> 00:04:24.583
[Fadly] I haven't really thought about it.

00:04:24.666 --> 00:04:26.500
I think she wants to pursue
a master's degree.

00:04:26.583 --> 00:04:29.541
[Mustafa huffs] Her dowry will get higher!

00:04:37.583 --> 00:04:40.125
[photographer] Ready? One, two, three.

00:04:40.208 --> 00:04:42.791
Again. One, two, three.

00:04:42.875 --> 00:04:44.208
THREE YEARS LATER

00:04:44.541 --> 00:04:45.500
Thank you.

00:04:45.583 --> 00:04:47.500
-Excuse me.
-Okay.

00:04:49.416 --> 00:04:50.625
[exclaims softly] Wow.

00:04:51.250 --> 00:04:53.083
-Looks good.
-So romantic.

00:04:55.958 --> 00:04:57.708
[sighs in relief]

00:04:59.541 --> 00:05:00.791
Thank God.

00:05:00.875 --> 00:05:02.875
GRAND OPENING OF SINRILIK MUSIC STUDIO
MUSICAL INSTRUMENT STORE

00:05:02.958 --> 00:05:03.875
Babe.

00:05:04.875 --> 00:05:07.500
Your dream finally came true.

00:05:08.333 --> 00:05:09.583
Thanks to God.

00:05:10.583 --> 00:05:12.166
Thank you, my love,

00:05:12.250 --> 00:05:15.708
for being there for me from the start.

00:05:16.583 --> 00:05:21.166
We'll be able to sing and practice here.

00:05:22.041 --> 00:05:23.583
We'll stay together forever?

00:05:24.208 --> 00:05:26.041
You want to stay with me forever?

00:05:26.125 --> 00:05:28.041
[laughs teasingly]

00:05:28.125 --> 00:05:30.041
-How sweet.
-[Nisa laughs teasingly]

00:05:31.250 --> 00:05:33.083
Fadly, this is great.

00:05:33.166 --> 00:05:34.541
Kallang can practice here.

00:05:35.708 --> 00:05:38.958
Don't miss dinner tonight
with Mom and Dad.

00:05:39.708 --> 00:05:40.625
At seven, right?

00:05:40.708 --> 00:05:42.458
-Don't forget.
-You got it.

00:05:43.041 --> 00:05:45.083
-See you, Nisa. Bye.
-Bye.

00:05:45.166 --> 00:05:48.541
[off-key humming]

00:05:49.791 --> 00:05:50.958
Hey.

00:05:51.041 --> 00:05:53.375
Even your humming is off-key.

00:05:53.958 --> 00:05:56.000
Don't overdo it
when all you know is the C chord.

00:05:56.083 --> 00:05:58.583
How do you know, Ariping? Look!

00:05:59.583 --> 00:06:01.000
I know the E chord.

00:06:01.083 --> 00:06:02.875
I'm just learning more skills.

00:06:02.958 --> 00:06:05.916
Besides, I'm already the master
of wiring and gear setup.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:07.291
Not to brag,

00:06:08.541 --> 00:06:09.583
just facts!

00:06:09.666 --> 00:06:11.583
Says the one who got zapped yesterday.

00:06:11.666 --> 00:06:13.083
[laughing]

00:06:13.166 --> 00:06:15.916
I mean, with open wires and sweaty palms?

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:17.083
It's a given.

00:06:18.458 --> 00:06:20.000
-Hello, Nisa.
-Hello.

00:06:20.083 --> 00:06:21.875
Come on, what do you know?

00:06:21.958 --> 00:06:24.291
I know my stuff.

00:06:25.291 --> 00:06:26.833
[man] Peace be upon you.

00:06:26.916 --> 00:06:28.583
And upon you peace.

00:06:29.208 --> 00:06:30.625
Congrats, Fad.

00:06:30.708 --> 00:06:34.583
I'm glad everything went well today.

00:06:34.666 --> 00:06:40.708
I want to thank you again for your support

00:06:40.791 --> 00:06:45.666
and for letting me pay the rent monthly.

00:06:46.458 --> 00:06:48.416
You're welcome, Fadly.

00:06:48.500 --> 00:06:52.750
I used to be young and full of ego myself,

00:06:52.833 --> 00:06:54.500
so I get it.

00:06:54.583 --> 00:06:58.375
Besides, my place won't be empty anymore.

00:06:58.458 --> 00:06:59.583
[chuckles]

00:06:59.666 --> 00:07:01.916
I hope this business goes well.

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:03.375
Hope you pay rent on time too.

00:07:03.458 --> 00:07:05.416
[laughing]

00:07:06.166 --> 00:07:07.041
Hi, Nisa.

00:07:07.125 --> 00:07:08.875
-Sir.
-Hi.

00:07:08.958 --> 00:07:12.458
You're a charming guy,
and she's a lovely lady.

00:07:12.541 --> 00:07:13.916
What are you waiting for?

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:15.166
[chuckles]

00:07:15.958 --> 00:07:18.666
Wish me luck for that, sir.

00:07:18.750 --> 00:07:20.250
Sure, Amen.

00:07:20.333 --> 00:07:21.416
Right, babe?

00:07:22.875 --> 00:07:24.083
Who's inside?

00:07:24.625 --> 00:07:27.041
Tell them off. They're always bickering.

00:07:28.041 --> 00:07:29.416
What are you playing?

00:07:31.333 --> 00:07:32.833
[clapping]

00:07:32.916 --> 00:07:36.333
I know you've got talent, Fadly.

00:07:36.416 --> 00:07:38.875
I'm sure you'll be
the next Ridwan Budiman.

00:07:38.958 --> 00:07:40.208
Who?

00:07:40.291 --> 00:07:42.333
My uncle. He sings really well.

00:07:42.416 --> 00:07:43.458
He's from Kendari.

00:07:44.458 --> 00:07:47.500
What? You look like
you're looking down on me.

00:07:47.583 --> 00:07:49.541
Because I am looking down on you.

00:07:49.625 --> 00:07:50.583
Hey.

00:07:51.500 --> 00:07:53.166
Speaking of which,

00:07:53.250 --> 00:07:54.791
I think

00:07:56.208 --> 00:07:57.625
I want to propose to Nisa.

00:07:57.708 --> 00:07:59.791
Praise be to God!

00:07:59.875 --> 00:08:01.333
[exclaiming] Thank God!

00:08:01.416 --> 00:08:04.041
Look at him, Ariping.
He's about to get married.

00:08:04.125 --> 00:08:05.916
-What about you?
-Look who's talking.

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:08.583
You're paying for a premium dating app,
but still no girlfriend.

00:08:08.666 --> 00:08:10.250
[laughing]

00:08:10.333 --> 00:08:12.833
The app is just broken.

00:08:12.916 --> 00:08:14.208
But seriously, when?

00:08:14.291 --> 00:08:15.500
But…

00:08:15.583 --> 00:08:16.625
Huh?

00:08:17.500 --> 00:08:18.375
A three-in-one wedding?

00:08:18.458 --> 00:08:20.958
Kifly is going to propose
to his girlfriend, Karin.

00:08:21.041 --> 00:08:25.458
I figured you'd all get married in
a three-in-one wedding.

00:08:25.541 --> 00:08:28.375
I also talked to Mom,

00:08:28.458 --> 00:08:29.875
and she agreed.

00:08:29.958 --> 00:08:31.708
But… Mom.

00:08:32.500 --> 00:08:33.750
Why?

00:08:33.833 --> 00:08:35.666
You all know,

00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:39.375
I'm past the age of earning money,

00:08:39.916 --> 00:08:44.708
but the dowry and wedding expenses
are getting higher.

00:08:45.166 --> 00:08:47.791
I've saved 300 million.

00:08:47.875 --> 00:08:51.000
It should be enough for your dowry,

00:08:51.916 --> 00:08:54.833
engagement, and wedding reception costs.

00:08:55.500 --> 00:08:56.541
But Dad,

00:08:57.500 --> 00:08:59.708
why can't have get our own weddings?

00:08:59.791 --> 00:09:01.291
We can earn the money ourselves.

00:09:01.375 --> 00:09:02.833
I'm saving up as well.

00:09:02.916 --> 00:09:06.375
Fadly, listen. In our culture,

00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:10.791
parents are responsible
for arranging their child's marriage.

00:09:11.416 --> 00:09:17.791
If I can't do it with my resources,

00:09:17.875 --> 00:09:19.791
I feel like I've failed.

00:09:19.875 --> 00:09:23.833
How long do I have to wait
for you to be financially stable?

00:09:23.916 --> 00:09:25.250
Until I'm dead?

00:09:25.333 --> 00:09:26.583
-Oh my God.
-Dear!

00:09:27.666 --> 00:09:29.916
How could you say that?

00:09:30.000 --> 00:09:31.166
Yeah, Dad.

00:09:31.250 --> 00:09:33.500
[Mustafa] Just trust me.

00:09:33.583 --> 00:09:36.333
Fadly, talk to Nisa.

00:09:37.125 --> 00:09:39.708
Kifly, talk to Karin.

00:09:39.791 --> 00:09:42.250
And Ahmad, talk to Asha.

00:09:42.333 --> 00:09:44.375
You're all going to propose this month.

00:09:44.458 --> 00:09:45.791
What?

00:09:45.875 --> 00:09:47.791
Are you two sure about this?

00:09:47.875 --> 00:09:49.833
[Mustafa] I've arranged everything.

00:09:49.916 --> 00:09:53.000
Next week, we'll go to Solo
to propose to Karin.

00:09:53.541 --> 00:09:56.541
After that, to Sengkang for Nisa.

00:09:57.125 --> 00:10:00.333
And finally, Jakarta for Asha.

00:10:03.041 --> 00:10:04.000
Mom…

00:10:04.625 --> 00:10:06.125
It's okay, son.

00:10:06.208 --> 00:10:09.916
You've all been in
steady relationships long enough.

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:13.875
There's no harm in getting married now.

00:10:14.916 --> 00:10:18.291
What about Ahmad's girlfriend?
Does she want to?

00:10:18.375 --> 00:10:21.208
How did you come to that conclusion?
He's not done talking.

00:10:21.291 --> 00:10:24.041
Just trust me.
My feelings are never wrong.

00:10:24.125 --> 00:10:25.000
Wanna bet on it?

00:10:25.083 --> 00:10:25.916
Do you?

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:26.875
[Pirre chuckles]

00:10:26.958 --> 00:10:28.125
Give me that.

00:10:29.291 --> 00:10:32.416
-The loser has to eat this.
-Everything?

00:10:32.500 --> 00:10:34.083
Yes, everything. You scared?

00:10:34.166 --> 00:10:36.375
-Okay, deal.
-Deal!

00:10:37.875 --> 00:10:39.250
I'd love to.

00:10:39.333 --> 00:10:40.208
Really?

00:10:40.291 --> 00:10:41.833
Of course. Who would say no to a proposal

00:10:41.916 --> 00:10:46.458
from the handsome
young lecturer Ahmad Mustafa?

00:10:46.541 --> 00:10:47.500
[crunch]

00:10:48.166 --> 00:10:51.250
[wheezing, laughing]

00:10:51.333 --> 00:10:52.541
[Fadly] Enough.

00:10:53.458 --> 00:10:56.375
Wish me luck, guys.

00:10:57.000 --> 00:11:00.333
Let's hope Nisa and her family
will accept my proposal.

00:11:00.416 --> 00:11:01.875
We'll pray for you.

00:11:01.958 --> 00:11:05.208
May Nisa accept Fadly's proposal. Amen.

00:11:06.708 --> 00:11:09.500
[Kifly] So here's the concept.

00:11:09.916 --> 00:11:12.250
The balloons will go there…

00:11:12.333 --> 00:11:17.416
If you have no more questions,
I'll send the final draft tonight.

00:11:17.500 --> 00:11:19.125
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

00:11:19.208 --> 00:11:20.083
[woman] Bye.

00:11:20.166 --> 00:11:21.708
[Kifly] Adi, Aldhy. Is everything good?

00:11:21.791 --> 00:11:23.875
-All good.
-All right.

00:11:23.958 --> 00:11:26.750
We can't afford any mistakes.

00:11:26.833 --> 00:11:30.166
This is important for our portfolio
and the client's trust.

00:11:30.250 --> 00:11:33.625
Are you sure you don't need a rain shaman?

00:11:34.500 --> 00:11:36.250
We don't need it.

00:11:36.333 --> 00:11:39.291
Just in case you change your mind,

00:11:39.375 --> 00:11:41.583
my uncle is a rain shaman.

00:11:42.208 --> 00:11:44.375
I thought your uncle sold coconuts
at Losari Beach?

00:11:44.458 --> 00:11:46.458
That's his main job.

00:11:46.541 --> 00:11:49.666
But he can be a rain shaman if needed.

00:11:49.750 --> 00:11:51.291
He's got a range of skills.

00:11:51.375 --> 00:11:54.041
AC repairs, fan repairs,

00:11:54.125 --> 00:11:55.333
and even contractor jobs.

00:11:55.416 --> 00:11:56.625
-A contractor?
-That's right.

00:11:56.708 --> 00:11:59.041
He used to work as a firefighter.

00:11:59.125 --> 00:12:00.166
-A firefighter?
-Yes.

00:12:00.250 --> 00:12:02.041
Handled washing bodies at funerals.

00:12:02.125 --> 00:12:03.750
He can also install ceilings.

00:12:04.250 --> 00:12:05.166
Ceiling installation too.

00:12:05.250 --> 00:12:07.291
-Your uncle is amazing.
-He is.

00:12:07.375 --> 00:12:10.916
Anyway, now we just need
to take care of the food and the tent.

00:12:11.458 --> 00:12:12.458
-Right.
-Got it.

00:12:12.541 --> 00:12:15.625
We'll check the food portions…

00:12:15.708 --> 00:12:17.791
Let me see.

00:12:17.875 --> 00:12:19.083
I can do…

00:12:20.083 --> 00:12:21.416
Good afternoon.

00:12:21.500 --> 00:12:22.875
You're here?

00:12:22.958 --> 00:12:27.541
This place is on my way home,
so I figured I'd stop by.

00:12:27.625 --> 00:12:29.458
-How is it going?
-[both] All good.

00:12:29.958 --> 00:12:31.375
We should get going, Doc.

00:12:32.333 --> 00:12:33.416
Sit down.

00:12:34.500 --> 00:12:37.625
Hello. I got you coffee.

00:12:37.708 --> 00:12:38.958
Refreshments.

00:12:39.041 --> 00:12:40.416
Thanks, babe.

00:12:40.500 --> 00:12:42.041
[gentle music]

00:12:42.125 --> 00:12:43.250
What is this?

00:12:46.791 --> 00:12:49.083
What's with that grin?

00:12:49.916 --> 00:12:51.708
[hums]

00:12:52.875 --> 00:12:55.541
Are you curious, or super curious?

00:12:55.625 --> 00:12:56.708
Super curious.

00:12:56.791 --> 00:12:58.333
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

00:12:58.416 --> 00:12:59.625
-[giggles]
-What?

00:12:59.708 --> 00:13:00.791
So…

00:13:01.416 --> 00:13:03.583
My assignment changed.
I'm not going to Bali.

00:13:04.125 --> 00:13:05.166
Okay.

00:13:05.666 --> 00:13:08.041
I'm assigned to…

00:13:09.333 --> 00:13:10.208
Makassar!

00:13:10.791 --> 00:13:13.083
-Makassar? Really?
-Yeah, Makassar!

00:13:13.166 --> 00:13:14.291
Yes!

00:13:14.375 --> 00:13:15.250
[chuckles]

00:13:15.333 --> 00:13:16.541
How come? Tell me.

00:13:16.625 --> 00:13:20.666
That's what you get
for having a diligent girlfriend

00:13:20.750 --> 00:13:22.625
who's never late

00:13:22.708 --> 00:13:26.625
and never says no to covering shifts.

00:13:27.208 --> 00:13:28.458
My girlfriend is amazing.

00:13:28.541 --> 00:13:30.208
[chuckles]

00:13:30.291 --> 00:13:31.625
Well.

00:13:31.708 --> 00:13:35.500
Since I won't be stationed in Bali,

00:13:36.750 --> 00:13:38.791
after we get married,

00:13:39.708 --> 00:13:41.083
let's go there for our honeymoon.

00:13:42.208 --> 00:13:44.541
Forget Bali, we're going to Europe.

00:13:44.625 --> 00:13:45.708
-Really?
-Just kidding.

00:13:45.791 --> 00:13:49.625
-I'm joking.
-Then I'll let my parents know.

00:13:49.708 --> 00:13:52.791
-My little sisters… You have a suitcase?
-I'm kidding.

00:13:53.625 --> 00:13:54.833
Let's save up.

00:13:55.666 --> 00:13:56.791
You promise?

00:13:58.041 --> 00:13:59.333
-I promise.
-Promise?

00:14:00.125 --> 00:14:01.708
-Yes.
-Fine.

00:14:02.625 --> 00:14:06.166
["Bersamamu" by Jaz playing]

00:14:10.500 --> 00:14:11.333
[phone dings]

00:14:13.875 --> 00:14:14.708
Wait.

00:14:15.583 --> 00:14:19.500
ASHA: BABE, MY PARENTS AGREED
TO YOUR PROPOSAL NEXT WEEK.

00:14:19.583 --> 00:14:21.916
[Fadly] A special smoothie

00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:26.375
for the princess who's come
a long way from Sengkang.

00:14:26.458 --> 00:14:27.458
Thanks, babe.

00:14:27.541 --> 00:14:29.000
Enjoy.

00:14:31.041 --> 00:14:32.416
-[hums]
-[sighs]

00:14:38.333 --> 00:14:42.791
Any news from your parents
about the three-in-one wedding plan?

00:14:46.041 --> 00:14:47.041
Well?

00:14:51.750 --> 00:14:53.375
My parents

00:14:53.458 --> 00:14:54.500
agreed.

00:14:54.583 --> 00:14:58.250
Thank God.

00:14:58.958 --> 00:15:00.250
Really?

00:15:02.083 --> 00:15:03.333
Thank God.

00:15:03.958 --> 00:15:05.416
I should tell my mom.

00:15:14.666 --> 00:15:15.833
What's the matter?

00:15:16.833 --> 00:15:17.833
It's nothing.

00:15:17.916 --> 00:15:19.833
-You sure?
-Yeah.

00:15:24.875 --> 00:15:26.791
HEADMASTER OF PAROPO INPRES
PUBLIC ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

00:15:26.875 --> 00:15:31.416
Kifly, come on. We're both ready.

00:15:34.750 --> 00:15:36.000
-Mom.
-What?

00:15:36.083 --> 00:15:38.208
We're bringing everything?

00:15:38.708 --> 00:15:40.000
Yeah.

00:15:40.083 --> 00:15:41.416
This is coto.

00:15:41.500 --> 00:15:44.041
Careful, don't spill it.

00:15:44.125 --> 00:15:47.375
This is jalangkote, and this is barongko.

00:15:47.458 --> 00:15:50.833
I made this for your future in-laws.

00:15:50.916 --> 00:15:53.041
We're only in Solo for one night.

00:15:53.125 --> 00:15:55.958
And the coto broth won't make it
through airport security.

00:15:56.041 --> 00:15:59.375
Don't worry. I'll handle it.

00:15:59.458 --> 00:16:01.458
But, I mean…

00:16:02.041 --> 00:16:05.125
Why so many suitcases?

00:16:05.208 --> 00:16:06.333
Kifly.

00:16:06.416 --> 00:16:10.625
In case your future in-laws give us gifts,

00:16:10.708 --> 00:16:14.166
you put them in here. Got it?

00:16:14.250 --> 00:16:16.458
[bright music]

00:16:23.416 --> 00:16:27.333
-[Fatimah] Peace be upon you.
-And upon you peace.

00:16:27.416 --> 00:16:29.000
How are you?

00:16:29.666 --> 00:16:33.333
[indistinct chatter]

00:16:34.625 --> 00:16:36.958
We have a small gift for you. Coto.

00:16:37.666 --> 00:16:40.833
I appreciate the effort, thank you.

00:16:40.916 --> 00:16:42.791
-Please, come in.
-Thank you.

00:16:44.500 --> 00:16:48.875
[in Javanese] It's a pleasure
to welcome you and your family.

00:16:48.958 --> 00:16:50.125
[chuckles awkwardly]

00:16:50.208 --> 00:16:53.791
Do you speak Indonesian?
We don't understand.

00:16:53.875 --> 00:16:56.875
Right, sorry. I'm just messing with you.

00:16:56.958 --> 00:17:01.166
[in Javanese] I can't believe an adult
can't speak Javanese.

00:17:01.250 --> 00:17:05.333
[in Makassarese] He thinks
everyone speaks Javanese?

00:17:05.416 --> 00:17:08.291
Javanese people may be everywhere,

00:17:08.375 --> 00:17:12.458
but not everyone has to know the language.

00:17:12.541 --> 00:17:14.708
[in Indonesian] Right,
let's speak Indonesian then.

00:17:14.791 --> 00:17:16.583
You really went there, huh?

00:17:16.666 --> 00:17:18.500
-[dads chuckling]
-[Karin's mom] Come on.

00:17:18.583 --> 00:17:21.000
Come in. It's hot outside.

00:17:21.083 --> 00:17:22.375
Come inside.

00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:23.666
[Mustafa] So,

00:17:23.750 --> 00:17:30.083
this is just to confirm and to reassure.

00:17:31.833 --> 00:17:34.666
You don't mind

00:17:34.750 --> 00:17:38.500
our kids having a joint wedding?

00:17:38.583 --> 00:17:40.625
It's all right.

00:17:40.708 --> 00:17:43.041
-We'll comply.
-Thank goodness.

00:17:43.125 --> 00:17:47.958
What's important is Kifly's
genuine intention to marry Karin.

00:17:48.041 --> 00:17:48.875
Of course.

00:17:48.958 --> 00:17:51.541
-The ceremony is what counts.
-Right.

00:17:51.625 --> 00:17:55.666
The reception is just a celebration.

00:17:55.750 --> 00:17:57.291
[chuckles] I agree.

00:17:57.375 --> 00:18:01.708
By the way, the reception is in
less than two months, right?

00:18:01.791 --> 00:18:03.083
God willing, yes.

00:18:03.166 --> 00:18:05.625
-[Karin's dad] Thank God.
-[Mustafa] Yes.

00:18:05.708 --> 00:18:07.708
[Mustafa] I hope
everything's ready by then.

00:18:07.791 --> 00:18:08.916
[Karin's dad] Yes.

00:18:09.541 --> 00:18:13.083
[man's voice] There's a guy
who's coming to propose to Nisa,

00:18:13.166 --> 00:18:15.875
but he could only afford 50 million
for the dowry.

00:18:15.958 --> 00:18:18.916
-[laughing]
-He's right.

00:18:19.000 --> 00:18:20.666
It's unclear what he does for a living.

00:18:20.750 --> 00:18:23.666
He's neither a civil servant
nor a policeman.

00:18:23.750 --> 00:18:24.583
What is he, then?

00:18:24.666 --> 00:18:26.125
He's in a Makassar-based band.

00:18:26.208 --> 00:18:29.000
-[mocking laughter]
-That doesn't make money.

00:18:29.083 --> 00:18:32.000
If I may, Puang,
ask them to raise the dowry.

00:18:32.083 --> 00:18:33.916
-Yes.
-Only then will I give my blessing.

00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:37.958
50 million isn't enough
to cover wedding expenses.

00:18:38.041 --> 00:18:39.208
[all chorusing] Right.

00:18:39.291 --> 00:18:44.250
Especially with how expensive
things are these days.

00:18:44.333 --> 00:18:48.000
[lady] Imagine what
the neighbors would say.

00:18:48.083 --> 00:18:52.833
Daeng Erang's daughter, a widow,
got a dowry of 80 million.

00:18:52.916 --> 00:18:57.458
Actually, Haji Tauhid's son has been
wanting to propose to Nisa for a while.

00:18:57.541 --> 00:19:00.583
I told her so, but she ignored it.

00:19:00.666 --> 00:19:03.291
Dowry won't be an issue with him.

00:19:03.375 --> 00:19:08.541
But listen, let our child choose
her own partner.

00:19:08.625 --> 00:19:11.208
-Parents must be involved.
-[woman] That's right.

00:19:11.291 --> 00:19:16.833
I won't let my only daughter
struggle in the future.

00:19:16.916 --> 00:19:19.833
I don't want my daughter to be miserable

00:19:19.916 --> 00:19:22.500
because she married someone
she doesn't love.

00:19:22.583 --> 00:19:26.000
[exclaims, laughs]

00:19:26.083 --> 00:19:29.041
Are you saying you've felt miserable
being with me

00:19:29.125 --> 00:19:31.041
because we had an arranged marriage?

00:19:31.375 --> 00:19:32.125
Listen.

00:19:32.208 --> 00:19:38.291
I can make my family happier than
your ex, who's now struggling!

00:19:39.333 --> 00:19:41.583
That's the whole point of the dowry.

00:19:41.666 --> 00:19:45.625
[Nisa's dad] To preserve
our family's dignity and nobility,

00:19:45.708 --> 00:19:50.458
and to vet potential husbands
and see who is serious!

00:19:50.541 --> 00:19:53.500
-[Nisa sniffling]
-[argument inside continues indistinctly]

00:19:55.625 --> 00:20:01.250
[somber music]

00:20:05.291 --> 00:20:09.000
Let's hope the song gets popular
and goes viral.

00:20:09.083 --> 00:20:10.250
[chuckles]

00:20:10.833 --> 00:20:12.916
Yes, you can always count on me.

00:20:14.541 --> 00:20:15.708
Yes, thank you.

00:20:15.791 --> 00:20:17.833
-[Fatimah] Take it out of the car.
-Okay.

00:20:17.916 --> 00:20:20.083
-Peace be upon you.
-[Fadly] And upon you peace. Mom!

00:20:20.166 --> 00:20:22.083
-It's raining. Come on.
-Yeah.

00:20:22.166 --> 00:20:24.333
Help your brother.

00:20:24.958 --> 00:20:27.083
-Dad.
-Yeah.

00:20:27.166 --> 00:20:28.333
Give Dad the umbrella.

00:20:28.416 --> 00:20:32.041
[Fatimah] Dear! You'll catch a cold.

00:20:32.125 --> 00:20:35.083
-Thank God.
-Thank God.

00:20:35.166 --> 00:20:37.291
-We're finally home.
-[Fatimah] Gosh.

00:20:37.375 --> 00:20:40.708
Why didn't you tell me you were coming?
I could've picked you up.

00:20:41.291 --> 00:20:43.500
With what? Your motorcycle?

00:20:43.583 --> 00:20:46.500
-Our car is at the repair shop.
-[Fatimah] Give that to me.

00:20:47.958 --> 00:20:51.666
What matters is your little brother's
situation is settled.

00:20:51.750 --> 00:20:54.500
Now it's just you and Ahmad's.

00:20:54.583 --> 00:20:57.416
Look, I got a lot of souvenirs.

00:20:57.500 --> 00:21:00.541
There's even some in the suitcase
from our future in-laws.

00:21:00.625 --> 00:21:01.541
That's a lot.

00:21:01.625 --> 00:21:05.333
Fadly, just focus on your wedding.

00:21:05.416 --> 00:21:06.750
I know.

00:21:07.375 --> 00:21:09.000
-Where's your ring?
-[Fatimah] Where's Ahmad?

00:21:09.083 --> 00:21:10.916
-[chuckles]
-Go inside.

00:21:12.125 --> 00:21:15.625
[gentle music]

00:21:15.708 --> 00:21:17.708
I'll have iced coffee with palm sugar.

00:21:18.583 --> 00:21:19.416
You?

00:21:20.416 --> 00:21:21.541
Anything's fine.

00:21:28.333 --> 00:21:30.083
Any recommendations?

00:21:30.166 --> 00:21:31.291
[waitress] Anything's fine.

00:21:32.375 --> 00:21:33.625
Just kidding.

00:21:33.708 --> 00:21:35.000
Would you like to try our green tea?

00:21:41.958 --> 00:21:45.791
Okay. One iced coffee with palm sugar
and one green tea.

00:21:47.291 --> 00:21:48.958
-[waitress] Please wait.
-[Fadly] Sure.

00:21:57.041 --> 00:22:00.000
So what did your dad say?

00:22:00.083 --> 00:22:02.458
Has he picked a date

00:22:03.125 --> 00:22:05.541
for me and my family to come and propose?

00:22:12.625 --> 00:22:13.583
Nisa.

00:22:15.958 --> 00:22:16.791
Yes?

00:22:17.625 --> 00:22:18.666
What's wrong?

00:22:18.750 --> 00:22:20.250
Were you saying something?

00:22:21.708 --> 00:22:24.791
So when can my family come to your house?

00:22:24.875 --> 00:22:25.625
Oh.

00:22:25.708 --> 00:22:26.625
When?

00:22:27.291 --> 00:22:28.708
I'm not sure.

00:22:29.208 --> 00:22:30.500
He hasn't answered.

00:22:33.416 --> 00:22:36.000
I heard this month
isn't good for a proposal.

00:22:36.083 --> 00:22:36.958
[chuckles]

00:22:37.833 --> 00:22:39.000
What year is this?

00:22:39.958 --> 00:22:41.708
You still believe in that?

00:22:43.708 --> 00:22:45.333
Are you making fun of my family?

00:22:47.541 --> 00:22:48.708
What's with you?

00:22:50.458 --> 00:22:51.541
It's nothing.

00:23:01.375 --> 00:23:03.833
Mom, isn't this ring expensive?

00:23:03.916 --> 00:23:07.375
Let's not bring money into this.

00:23:07.458 --> 00:23:11.333
My daughter's smile is all that matters.

00:23:11.416 --> 00:23:12.791
[chuckles]

00:23:20.375 --> 00:23:21.416
Thanks.

00:23:21.500 --> 00:23:22.708
Enjoy.

00:23:33.375 --> 00:23:34.875
-Mom.
-Yes?

00:23:36.625 --> 00:23:37.666
You want coffee?

00:23:39.166 --> 00:23:42.625
No. I like this ring.

00:23:43.666 --> 00:23:44.833
Okay.

00:23:45.333 --> 00:23:46.625
I'll take this.

00:23:48.666 --> 00:23:51.625
[somber music]

00:23:54.083 --> 00:23:55.666
[engine splutters]

00:23:56.958 --> 00:23:57.791
[grunts]

00:23:58.833 --> 00:23:59.583
[clicks tongue]

00:24:00.291 --> 00:24:01.916
What now?

00:24:03.750 --> 00:24:05.375
[sighs]

00:24:09.125 --> 00:24:09.958
[blows]

00:24:10.583 --> 00:24:12.625
Why did the motorcycle break down?

00:24:14.666 --> 00:24:16.958
Hey, answer me!

00:24:18.125 --> 00:24:19.833
Answer when someone's talking.

00:24:21.500 --> 00:24:22.666
Don't ignore them!

00:24:22.750 --> 00:24:24.625
You think I wanted this to happen?

00:24:25.583 --> 00:24:26.875
What's with you?

00:24:33.916 --> 00:24:34.958
Miss, tissue?

00:24:49.958 --> 00:24:51.041
[sighs]

00:24:51.666 --> 00:24:52.375
Psst.

00:24:54.958 --> 00:24:56.583
What's up with Fadly?

00:24:56.666 --> 00:24:58.041
Did he have a fight with Nisa?

00:24:58.125 --> 00:24:59.000
[shushes] Shh!

00:25:00.541 --> 00:25:01.875
Psst, Fadly.

00:25:01.958 --> 00:25:04.833
Sorry, I don't mean to pry,

00:25:04.916 --> 00:25:06.708
but are you okay?

00:25:06.791 --> 00:25:07.958
[sighs]

00:25:16.458 --> 00:25:17.708
Actually,

00:25:19.041 --> 00:25:20.875
there's nothing wrong.

00:25:22.000 --> 00:25:26.833
But since things between Nisa and me
are getting serious,

00:25:26.916 --> 00:25:29.541
tiny problems can feel huge.

00:25:29.625 --> 00:25:31.500
That's true, Fadly.

00:25:31.583 --> 00:25:33.125
This is only before marriage.

00:25:33.208 --> 00:25:37.291
After marriage, many couples get divorced
over tiny things.

00:25:37.375 --> 00:25:40.625
Huh, really? Like what?

00:25:40.708 --> 00:25:42.083
You need an example?

00:25:42.166 --> 00:25:44.708
Have you been living under a rock?
Get out more!

00:25:44.791 --> 00:25:47.666
Go on, tell him.

00:25:47.750 --> 00:25:49.125
[witty music]

00:25:49.208 --> 00:25:50.875
I heard in Makassar Info,

00:25:50.958 --> 00:25:54.750
a husband divorced his wife
because her butt was dark.

00:25:54.833 --> 00:25:56.708
That's just her natural skin color.

00:25:57.916 --> 00:25:59.833
If he wanted white,
he should've picked a cow.

00:26:00.541 --> 00:26:01.916
You hear that?

00:26:02.000 --> 00:26:04.541
Even the AC setting
can tear a marriage apart.

00:26:04.625 --> 00:26:07.666
That's why communication is important.

00:26:09.541 --> 00:26:10.833
Just talk to her.

00:26:10.916 --> 00:26:13.125
[witty music]

00:26:13.208 --> 00:26:14.250
[Fadly] Peace be upon you.

00:26:14.333 --> 00:26:17.666
-And upon you peace.
-And upon you peace.

00:26:17.750 --> 00:26:19.958
Fadly. Sit down.

00:26:20.625 --> 00:26:22.166
Your mom wants to talk.

00:26:26.750 --> 00:26:28.541
You say it.

00:26:29.041 --> 00:26:29.958
What?

00:26:30.625 --> 00:26:32.000
You're drenched.

00:26:32.083 --> 00:26:34.291
Yeah. It's pouring outside.

00:26:39.333 --> 00:26:41.583
How did things go with you and Nisa?

00:26:42.666 --> 00:26:44.666
She went back to Sengkang

00:26:45.666 --> 00:26:47.791
to discuss things with her parents.

00:26:53.375 --> 00:26:56.000
If that's the case, great.

00:26:57.125 --> 00:26:59.208
You should go there too.

00:26:59.875 --> 00:27:04.500
Show her your good intentions

00:27:04.583 --> 00:27:07.083
and commitment towards her.

00:27:08.458 --> 00:27:10.625
If I leave now,

00:27:10.708 --> 00:27:12.916
it's a five-hour ride by motorcycle.

00:27:13.000 --> 00:27:14.791
I'd get there at night.

00:27:16.125 --> 00:27:17.375
For Nisa?

00:27:18.875 --> 00:27:21.041
That shouldn't be a problem.

00:27:22.416 --> 00:27:24.250
Your mom is right.

00:27:24.333 --> 00:27:27.041
Make sure you go tomorrow morning.

00:27:27.125 --> 00:27:30.375
[adventure music]

00:27:50.208 --> 00:27:51.708
[thunder crackles]

00:27:53.458 --> 00:27:56.500
[Nisa's uncle] Ladies and gentlemen
and all honored guests.

00:27:56.583 --> 00:27:58.416
On this joyous day,

00:27:58.500 --> 00:28:02.291
we, representing Nisa's extended family,

00:28:02.375 --> 00:28:05.125
gladly accept Agus's proposal

00:28:05.208 --> 00:28:09.166
with a dowry of 500 million rupiah.

00:28:09.250 --> 00:28:11.708
[crowd] Praise be to God.

00:28:11.791 --> 00:28:14.166
We have come to an agreement

00:28:14.250 --> 00:28:18.125
that both the marriage ceremony
and the reception

00:28:18.208 --> 00:28:21.375
will be on Wednesday, May 22, 2019.

00:28:22.833 --> 00:28:25.541
[voice fades]

00:28:38.833 --> 00:28:40.125
Here you go.

00:28:40.208 --> 00:28:43.750
Place it on the right. That's it.

00:28:43.833 --> 00:28:45.458
-Excuse me.
-Lor!

00:28:46.000 --> 00:28:47.291
Excuse me, sir.

00:28:47.958 --> 00:28:49.375
What was going on here?

00:28:49.458 --> 00:28:51.333
A marriage proposal.

00:28:51.416 --> 00:28:54.666
Tomorrow will be crazy.
The dowry is 500 million.

00:28:54.750 --> 00:28:55.583
Huh?

00:28:57.250 --> 00:28:59.041
[hushed] But I heard

00:28:59.125 --> 00:29:02.041
Nisa was already in a relationship.

00:29:04.375 --> 00:29:05.375
You should go in.

00:29:05.833 --> 00:29:07.541
That bastard!

00:29:07.625 --> 00:29:09.375
Calm down, dear.

00:29:09.458 --> 00:29:11.083
You want me to stay calm?

00:29:11.166 --> 00:29:13.958
Who's left humiliated
now that this has happened?

00:29:14.041 --> 00:29:14.833
I am!

00:29:14.916 --> 00:29:16.416
I'm sorry, Dad.

00:29:17.375 --> 00:29:19.916
I didn't know it would end up like this.

00:29:22.333 --> 00:29:25.500
I don't think I can participate
in the three-in-one wedding.

00:29:25.583 --> 00:29:29.333
You still have to get married!
Look for another partner!

00:29:29.416 --> 00:29:30.708
[Fatimah] Dear!

00:29:30.791 --> 00:29:32.500
How do you expect me to do that?

00:29:32.583 --> 00:29:35.250
How? We don't have much time!

00:29:35.333 --> 00:29:37.375
I don't care! Find another!

00:29:37.458 --> 00:29:42.791
Let them know my son is going to marry
someone better than Nisa!

00:29:42.875 --> 00:29:44.791
It doesn't work like that!

00:29:44.875 --> 00:29:46.000
-Fadly.
-Fadly!

00:29:47.458 --> 00:29:49.416
Don't just sit there! Go after him!

00:29:49.500 --> 00:29:50.333
Fadly.

00:29:52.208 --> 00:29:53.125
Fadly.

00:29:54.958 --> 00:29:56.125
[exhales]

00:29:57.000 --> 00:29:58.333
How can we help him?

00:29:59.625 --> 00:30:01.000
I don't know.

