00:37:52.708 --> 00:37:54.125
Completely different.

00:37:54.875 --> 00:37:58.708
[sighs] And she was also hard to talk to.

00:37:59.250 --> 00:38:01.958
Pirre sure picks some odd ones.

00:38:02.041 --> 00:38:05.125
We picked her together, it wasn't just me.

00:38:06.083 --> 00:38:08.791
[Ariping] Relax,
we'll help you find another match.

00:38:09.458 --> 00:38:10.833
Okay?

00:38:10.916 --> 00:38:12.000
[whispers] Psst.

00:38:12.083 --> 00:38:13.166
Your mom.

00:38:13.791 --> 00:38:14.625
[gasps]

00:38:15.750 --> 00:38:16.708
It's my mom.

00:38:18.958 --> 00:38:20.333
[witty music]

00:38:21.416 --> 00:38:23.208
[Fatimah] Come here, dear.

00:38:25.791 --> 00:38:27.583
Why are you here, Mom?

00:38:27.666 --> 00:38:31.375
I was just in the area
and thought I'd drop by.

00:38:31.458 --> 00:38:35.833
This is Alisa, my friend's daughter.

00:38:36.416 --> 00:38:39.041
She's a sweet kid,

00:38:39.125 --> 00:38:44.333
kind-hearted, can recite the Quran well,
is hardworking, and is very humble.

00:38:45.083 --> 00:38:47.041
-I'm Fadly.
-Alisa.

00:38:47.125 --> 00:38:48.166
She's in high school?

00:38:48.250 --> 00:38:50.041
You're about to graduate
from high school, right?

00:38:50.125 --> 00:38:51.125
-Yes, Aunty.
-Right.

00:38:51.208 --> 00:38:53.458
You're not planning to go to college?

00:38:53.541 --> 00:38:56.458
Why don't you exchange numbers?

00:38:56.541 --> 00:39:00.416
That way, you can chat
like this every day.

00:39:00.500 --> 00:39:01.708
What for?

00:39:02.708 --> 00:39:04.750
-Just talk.
-[grunts]

00:39:04.833 --> 00:39:07.541
You can give her my number, Mom.

00:39:07.625 --> 00:39:09.125
I don't have it memorized.

00:39:09.208 --> 00:39:11.541
Whose number have you memorized?

00:39:11.625 --> 00:39:13.083
[phone ringing]

00:39:13.166 --> 00:39:14.083
[chuckles]

00:39:14.166 --> 00:39:15.708
That's a sin.

00:39:15.791 --> 00:39:17.666
No, Mom. This is work.

00:39:18.166 --> 00:39:19.333
I'll see you at home.

00:39:19.416 --> 00:39:20.875
-[hums]
-[chuckles]

00:39:22.791 --> 00:39:24.041
Later.

00:39:24.125 --> 00:39:25.583
-Okay.
-[Fadly] Hello?

00:39:25.666 --> 00:39:28.125
He's not usually like this.
He's just busy.

00:39:28.208 --> 00:39:32.791
Sorry that the introduction was so brief.

00:39:35.125 --> 00:39:36.833
[somber acoustic]

00:39:37.708 --> 00:39:39.375
-He looks busy.
-[Fadly] I can handle it.

00:39:39.458 --> 00:39:41.375
We'll come again sometimes.

00:39:41.458 --> 00:39:42.791
Let's go home.

00:39:44.416 --> 00:39:45.416
[Fatimah] Well, Fad?

00:39:45.500 --> 00:39:46.875
What?

00:39:48.333 --> 00:39:49.458
It's hot.

00:39:50.083 --> 00:39:51.833
-Give it to me.
-Careful.

00:39:55.083 --> 00:39:56.333
Alisa.

00:39:57.208 --> 00:39:59.250
[Fatimah] She's a sweet girl.

00:40:00.041 --> 00:40:04.166
Her mom and I are close.

00:40:04.250 --> 00:40:08.458
It will be easier
to convince their family.

00:40:08.541 --> 00:40:11.416
Alisa can still continue her studies.

00:40:11.500 --> 00:40:13.416
She's got a lot ahead of her.

00:40:13.916 --> 00:40:16.791
Plus, she's not my type anyway.

00:40:17.750 --> 00:40:19.208
What, are you buying a house?

00:40:19.291 --> 00:40:22.291
You have to have a type
when choosing a partner.

00:40:22.375 --> 00:40:23.708
-[Ahmad] True.
-For compatibility.

00:40:23.791 --> 00:40:27.625
Come on, Fadly. We're running out of time.

00:40:27.708 --> 00:40:29.250
Your Mom is right.

