continues playing]

00:47:02.375 --> 00:47:04.666
Hey, Rifa! [chuckles]

00:47:04.750 --> 00:47:06.833
I can't believe you're here.

00:47:07.375 --> 00:47:08.666
No.

00:47:09.916 --> 00:47:12.958
Peace be upon you, Rifa.

00:47:14.958 --> 00:47:15.791
Fadly?

00:47:17.875 --> 00:47:19.375
-Fadly!
-Rifa.

00:47:19.458 --> 00:47:20.791
[Fadly laughs awkwardly]

00:47:21.416 --> 00:47:22.583
How long have you been here?

00:47:22.666 --> 00:47:25.208
I just got here. Are you by yourself?

00:47:25.291 --> 00:47:28.208
Where's your wife? She's not with you?

00:47:28.291 --> 00:47:29.208
Me?

00:47:30.083 --> 00:47:31.333
My wife?

00:47:31.416 --> 00:47:32.708
[giggles]

00:47:33.958 --> 00:47:35.583
I'm still single.

00:47:35.666 --> 00:47:36.500
Oh.

00:47:37.291 --> 00:47:38.541
You?

00:47:38.625 --> 00:47:40.666
Are you with your husband?

00:47:41.541 --> 00:47:42.458
[Rifa] Ah…

00:47:43.250 --> 00:47:45.208
I'm single too.

00:47:46.208 --> 00:47:47.375
Oh.

00:47:50.291 --> 00:47:51.416
What are you doing here?

00:47:52.041 --> 00:47:54.375
What a boring question.

00:47:54.458 --> 00:47:56.416
Isn't it obvious why I'm in a bookstore?

00:47:57.083 --> 00:47:59.083
[chuckles] Right.

00:48:02.041 --> 00:48:03.333
[clears throat]

00:48:04.833 --> 00:48:05.875
Fadly.

00:48:06.583 --> 00:48:08.000
What is that book?

00:48:09.250 --> 00:48:10.333
It's…

00:48:10.416 --> 00:48:11.416
HEALTHY RECIPES FOR THE FAMILY
30-DAY MEAL PLAN

00:48:11.500 --> 00:48:12.250
What is this?

00:48:12.333 --> 00:48:13.250
[stuttering] It's, um…

00:48:14.541 --> 00:48:15.750
My mom asked me to get this.

00:48:15.833 --> 00:48:18.541
Oh. I thought you were into cooking now.

00:48:18.625 --> 00:48:19.625
Not really.

00:48:19.708 --> 00:48:20.666
Tell your mom I said hi.

00:48:20.750 --> 00:48:22.416
Sure.

00:48:22.958 --> 00:48:24.000
Rifa.

00:48:24.875 --> 00:48:27.708
Do you still use your old number?

00:48:27.791 --> 00:48:29.125
Yeah, I still use it.

00:48:35.416 --> 00:48:36.541
[chuckles]

00:48:36.625 --> 00:48:39.416
Well then, I should get going.

00:48:44.000 --> 00:48:44.833
Fadly.

00:48:48.125 --> 00:48:50.625
[chuckles]

00:48:50.708 --> 00:48:51.958
-Bye.
-Bye.

00:48:52.625 --> 00:48:55.250
[bright music]

00:49:04.333 --> 00:49:07.833
[Ariping] Stop dwelling on it. Look ahead.

00:49:07.916 --> 00:49:08.791
[Pirre] Right.

00:49:08.875 --> 00:49:11.750
I'm sure Nisa isn't even
thinking about you anymore.

00:49:13.416 --> 00:49:14.750
Hey, boss.

00:49:14.833 --> 00:49:17.208
Any luck on the dating app?

00:49:17.791 --> 00:49:18.666
No?

00:49:19.125 --> 00:49:20.416
Should I introduce you to my friend?

00:49:20.500 --> 00:49:21.541
No, no!

00:49:22.000 --> 00:49:23.791
You know he's got weird taste.

00:49:23.875 --> 00:49:26.625
I'm serious. Just take a look.

00:49:27.458 --> 00:49:28.458
Ta-da.

00:49:29.000 --> 00:49:32.083
Pirre? He was my friend in high school.

00:49:32.166 --> 00:49:34.500
Oh, you were high school friends?

00:49:34.583 --> 00:49:35.958
[coughs, farts]

00:49:38.333 --> 00:49:39.333
[farts]

00:49:40.250 --> 00:49:41.291
Yes.

00:49:41.375 --> 00:49:44.958
Pirre and I work together.

00:49:45.041 --> 00:49:47.541
We've set up a small studio.

00:49:47.625 --> 00:49:48.833
Sounds fun.

00:49:49.833 --> 00:49:51.458
[laughs, farts]

00:49:51.541 --> 00:49:53.125
[clears throat]

00:49:58.125 --> 00:49:59.083
[farts]

00:49:59.625 --> 00:50:00.625
Are you sick?

00:50:00.708 --> 00:50:02.208
No. [farts]

00:50:02.291 --> 00:50:03.208
[grunts]

00:50:03.291 --> 00:50:05.333
You set me up with a fart machine?

00:50:05.416 --> 00:50:07.958
[cackles]

00:50:08.041 --> 00:50:10.875
Actually, I used to be close with her,

00:50:10.958 --> 00:50:13.333
but she was obsessed with salted eggs,

00:50:13.416 --> 00:50:15.208
which made her fart a lot.

00:50:15.291 --> 00:50:17.750
Whatever. You're driving me crazy.

00:50:17.833 --> 00:50:18.708
[phone buzzing]

00:50:18.791 --> 00:50:21.875
What a bad friend. You set him up.

00:50:23.875 --> 00:50:24.791
Hey.

00:50:25.416 --> 00:50:27.166
What was your ex's name again?

00:50:27.875 --> 00:50:28.666
Rifa?

00:50:29.250 --> 00:50:30.708
She's not my ex.

00:50:31.500 --> 00:50:32.666
Just a friend.

00:50:34.208 --> 00:50:35.833
I wasn't that confident.

00:50:35.916 --> 00:50:37.708
Why?

00:50:37.791 --> 00:50:42.416
If Nisa's family didn't want me
as a son-in-law,

00:50:42.500 --> 00:50:44.458
Rifa's parents definitely won't.

00:50:44.541 --> 00:50:48.208
You know the biggest rice factory
in Sidrap?

00:50:48.291 --> 00:50:49.208
Yeah?

00:50:49.291 --> 00:50:50.083
It's her uncle's.

00:50:50.166 --> 00:50:53.000
And the Mutiara City housing complexes

00:50:53.083 --> 00:50:54.958
in Makassar,

00:50:55.041 --> 00:50:57.458
Kendari, Parepare, Manado,

00:50:57.541 --> 00:50:59.083
and the new one in Bali?

00:50:59.750 --> 00:51:00.958
All owned by her father.

00:51:02.625 --> 00:51:04.083
What's her social media?

00:51:04.708 --> 00:51:06.000
What are you doing?

00:51:06.833 --> 00:51:08.625
Who knows? She could be into me.

00:51:08.708 --> 00:51:11.833
Fadly's way better than you.

00:51:11.916 --> 00:51:13.625
While you look like this.

00:51:14.458 --> 00:51:17.041
When you don't try,
you only have one outcome.

00:51:17.125 --> 00:51:18.041
Failure.

00:51:18.125 --> 00:51:20.291
But if you try, it's 50-50.

00:51:20.375 --> 00:51:22.083
Success or failure.

00:51:22.166 --> 00:51:23.500
[Malik] Pirre is right.

00:51:24.375 --> 00:51:25.791
Mr. Malik.

00:51:25.875 --> 00:51:26.958
Amazing.

00:51:27.041 --> 00:51:28.041
Sir.

00:51:28.583 --> 00:51:29.750
Go ahead.

00:51:31.625 --> 00:51:33.250
Why not give it a shot?

00:51:38.125 --> 00:51:40.541
You're almost out of time.

00:51:41.125 --> 00:51:42.791
You've got to make a move.

00:51:43.791 --> 00:51:45.125
I know, sir.

00:51:46.125 --> 00:51:47.291
But…

00:51:47.375 --> 00:51:48.166
[clicks tongue]

00:51:49.000 --> 00:51:51.958
It's heavy. I'm still traumatized.

00:51:54.708 --> 00:51:55.958
Do you know

00:51:57.041 --> 00:51:58.875
what knowledge is the most important?

00:52:00.291 --> 00:52:01.166
What?

00:52:01.666 --> 00:52:04.083
The most important knowledge

00:52:04.166 --> 00:52:07.083
is one where you understand yourself.

00:52:08.041 --> 00:52:12.333
How well you understand your capabilities.

00:52:12.416 --> 00:52:14.500
Your weaknesses

00:52:15.916 --> 00:52:17.583
and your strengths.

00:52:18.375 --> 00:52:23.250
Humans are God's greatest creation,

00:52:23.333 --> 00:52:26.625
and it's up to us to make the most of it

00:52:26.708 --> 00:52:29.458
to grow our goodness.

00:52:32.333 --> 00:52:34.500
Even the worst of people

00:52:35.041 --> 00:52:37.750
seek out good ones.

00:52:38.250 --> 00:52:39.875
And being a good person

00:52:40.875 --> 00:52:43.666
is your strength.

00:52:43.750 --> 00:52:46.791
[tender music]

00:52:46.875 --> 00:52:47.791
[chuckles]

00:52:57.375 --> 00:52:59.916
[Fatimah] Dear, what should we do?

00:53:00.000 --> 00:53:04.625
We must send out the invitations now.
We're running out of time.

00:53:04.708 --> 00:53:07.916
[Mustafa] Well, what can we do?

00:53:09.916 --> 00:53:11.958
Fadly hasn't found his match.

00:53:13.791 --> 00:53:15.208
[Fatimah] What if

00:53:16.083 --> 00:53:18.916
we postpone Fadly's wedding for now?

00:53:19.000 --> 00:53:20.416
No!

00:53:21.000 --> 00:53:22.041
No way!

00:53:22.125 --> 00:53:24.458
How can I keep my honor?

00:53:25.916 --> 00:53:30.208
Plus, Nisa's family
will just get more arrogant.

00:53:31.208 --> 00:53:32.791
[Mustafa] Dear, you know

00:53:33.666 --> 00:53:36.750
I can only afford one wedding.

00:53:38.000 --> 00:53:43.041
[Fatimah] But what if Fadly
is still heartbroken?

00:53:44.500 --> 00:53:45.916
He hasn't healed.

00:53:46.000 --> 00:53:49.041
Wounds can be healed
if we push through them.

00:53:49.625 --> 00:53:50.958
No need to spoil him.

00:53:52.875 --> 00:53:56.666
Wounds can be healed
if we push through them?

00:53:58.500 --> 00:53:59.500
[groans]

00:53:59.583 --> 00:54:01.833
-No need to spoil him.
-[groaning]

00:54:02.375 --> 00:54:03.541
[whines]

00:54:04.291 --> 00:54:06.666
[somber music]

00:54:10.166 --> 00:54:11.291
[sighs]

00:54:12.500 --> 00:54:15.458
Hi, how are you?

00:54:21.708 --> 00:54:23.083
[exhales]

00:54:27.083 --> 00:54:28.125
Fadly.

00:54:29.083 --> 00:54:31.791
Come here. I want to talk to you.

00:54:38.166 --> 00:54:39.375
[sighs]

00:54:39.458 --> 00:54:40.541
What's up, Dad?

00:54:42.541 --> 00:54:43.583
How is it going?

00:54:46.083 --> 00:54:48.166
How is what going?

00:54:51.000 --> 00:54:51.916
Oh.

00:54:52.583 --> 00:54:53.875
My studio?

00:54:55.291 --> 00:54:58.291
It's going well. We're making progress.

00:54:58.375 --> 00:55:02.500
Your studio is growing,
but you still can't find a partner.

00:55:05.375 --> 00:55:08.875
Marriage is
a once-in-a-lifetime commitment.

00:55:10.708 --> 00:55:12.833
I don't want to choose the wrong partner.

00:55:12.916 --> 00:55:17.041
But remember, time is running out.

00:55:18.000 --> 00:55:21.250
I'll introduce you to

00:55:22.208 --> 00:55:23.541
Aunty Ina's daughter.

00:55:27.000 --> 00:55:28.666
You want to set up an arranged marriage?

00:55:28.750 --> 00:55:31.208
It's not an arranged marriage.

00:55:31.291 --> 00:55:35.791
You're just meeting up.
She could be the one.

00:55:35.875 --> 00:55:37.333
You never know.

00:55:38.125 --> 00:55:39.541
[Fatimah] Yes, dear.

00:55:39.625 --> 00:55:41.166
Get to know each other first.

00:55:41.916 --> 00:55:45.625
Aunty Ina is my close friend.

00:55:45.708 --> 00:55:47.458
I know, Mom.

00:55:48.166 --> 00:55:51.416
But you only know Aunty Ina,
not her daughter.

00:55:51.916 --> 00:55:53.708
Yes, but…

00:55:54.708 --> 00:55:56.000
Wait.

00:55:57.125 --> 00:55:59.000
Look at this.

00:56:03.166 --> 00:56:04.208
Which one is she?

00:56:05.250 --> 00:56:08.041
That one.

00:56:13.875 --> 00:56:15.041
[sighs]

00:56:16.541 --> 00:56:19.958
That sour look on your face
reminds me of jalangkote sambal.

00:56:20.708 --> 00:56:22.666
That analogy feels off.

00:56:22.750 --> 00:56:24.541
Jalangkote is always sour.

00:56:26.041 --> 00:56:28.416
Come on, don't stress it, Fadly.

00:56:29.958 --> 00:56:33.000
I've had enough
of these matchmaking attempts.

00:56:33.083 --> 00:56:36.000
[Pirre] It's not matchmaking.
You're just meeting up.

00:56:36.083 --> 00:56:38.416
She could be the one. You never know.

00:56:39.416 --> 00:56:41.583
I think my dad said that too.

00:56:42.125 --> 00:56:45.333
[in deeper voice] "It's not matchmaking.
You're just meeting up."

00:56:45.416 --> 00:56:48.333
"She could be the one. You never know."

00:56:48.416 --> 00:56:50.916
[in normal voice]
Do I sound like Mr. Mustafa? [laughs]

00:56:52.208 --> 00:56:53.291
[man] Hey, Fadly!

00:56:54.125 --> 00:56:55.625
What's going on?

00:56:56.458 --> 00:56:59.541
Why are you still talking to Nisa?
She's engaged!

00:56:59.625 --> 00:57:01.208
I never contacted her.

00:57:01.291 --> 00:57:03.916
Talk to her again,
and I'll wreck this place.

00:57:04.000 --> 00:57:05.875
-[clamoring]
-Hey!

00:57:05.958 --> 00:57:07.166
Keep that in mind.

00:57:09.708 --> 00:57:10.833
[grunts]

00:57:10.916 --> 00:57:12.166
Hey, mophead!

00:57:12.250 --> 00:57:15.208
I've got more hair than you,
even though mine's an afro!

00:57:15.708 --> 00:57:16.791
Are you okay?

00:57:17.500 --> 00:57:20.166
Fadly, are you hurt anywhere?

00:57:20.250 --> 00:57:21.583
No, right?

00:57:21.666 --> 00:57:22.875
[grunts]

00:57:22.958 --> 00:57:24.166
That pisses me off!

00:57:24.250 --> 00:57:27.000
When I get mad, I start shaking.

00:57:27.083 --> 00:57:29.500
[Ina] Fatimah, how are you?

00:57:29.583 --> 00:57:31.833
Long time no see.

00:57:31.916 --> 00:57:35.458
It's been a while. I've been great.

00:57:35.541 --> 00:57:39.625
I believe it's been five years
since you moved.

00:57:39.708 --> 00:57:43.125
Yeah, I went with my husband
five years ago.

00:57:43.208 --> 00:57:44.833
-Right.
-Wait.

00:57:44.916 --> 00:57:48.458
Sri! Make some drinks for our guests.

00:57:48.541 --> 00:57:49.583
[Ina] Oh…

00:57:49.666 --> 00:57:51.875
How's Mustafa doing? Is he well?

00:57:51.958 --> 00:57:55.333
He's fine. But I'm sorry he couldn't come.

00:57:55.416 --> 00:57:57.083
He sends his regards.

00:57:57.166 --> 00:58:01.208
It's fine, I'm just glad
I met you after so long.

00:58:01.291 --> 00:58:03.791
[Fatimah] That's why
we should meet up more often.

00:58:03.875 --> 00:58:04.875
Of course.

00:58:04.958 --> 00:58:08.416
By the way, where's your child that
you want to introduce to Fadly?

00:58:08.500 --> 00:58:10.458
Gosh, I almost forgot.

00:58:10.541 --> 00:58:12.208
Here she is. Sri.

00:58:12.666 --> 00:58:13.458
[Fatimah] It's her?

00:58:13.541 --> 00:58:15.291
-Yes.
-Oh.

00:58:15.375 --> 00:58:18.333
You're beautiful. Sit with us.

00:58:18.416 --> 00:58:19.750
Take a seat.

00:58:20.750 --> 00:58:23.500
-Fadly, this is my daughter.
-[chuckling awkwardly]

00:58:23.583 --> 00:58:24.375
See?

00:58:24.458 --> 00:58:25.166
Fadly.

00:58:25.250 --> 00:58:26.541
Sri.

00:58:26.625 --> 00:58:27.458
Hi.

00:58:27.541 --> 00:58:30.000
Why? Are you confused?

00:58:31.166 --> 00:58:35.458
Sorry. That photo I sent you
was from ten years ago.

00:58:35.541 --> 00:58:36.416
[Fatimah] Oh.

00:58:36.500 --> 00:58:39.208
[Ina] Sri is my stepdaughter.

00:58:39.291 --> 00:58:41.625
She's a bit shy,

00:58:41.708 --> 00:58:43.791
so she doesn't have any recent pictures.

00:58:43.875 --> 00:58:46.625
-Fatimah, let's talk out the back.
-Yes?

00:58:46.708 --> 00:58:49.583
Let Fadly and Sri get to know each other.

00:58:50.375 --> 00:58:54.125
-[hums] Are you getting shy?
-No, I'm good. You can stay.

00:58:54.208 --> 00:58:56.625
It's okay, Fadly. Go talk to her.

00:58:56.708 --> 00:58:58.541
Don't go too long, Mom.
Dad needs his meds.

00:58:58.625 --> 00:59:00.750
[Fatimah] Okay, okay.

00:59:02.208 --> 00:59:04.541
-[sighs]
-[witty music]

00:59:04.625 --> 00:59:05.458
[chuckles]

00:59:08.708 --> 00:59:09.750
Help yourself.

00:59:16.291 --> 00:59:18.250
Such a classic taste.

00:59:18.333 --> 00:59:21.500
-[Fatimah] Peace be upon you.
-[both] And upon you peace.

00:59:21.583 --> 00:59:23.125
[Fatimah] What are you making?

00:59:23.208 --> 00:59:25.750
-Wedding invitations. Check it out.
-[Fatimah] Oh.

00:59:25.833 --> 00:59:26.875
[Fatimah] I love the colors.

00:59:26.958 --> 00:59:28.333
How did it go?

00:59:29.083 --> 00:59:30.625
How did it go?

00:59:31.541 --> 00:59:33.125
Ask Mom.

00:59:33.208 --> 00:59:34.791
[chuckles]

00:59:34.875 --> 00:59:37.000
Don't be mad at me.

00:59:37.541 --> 00:59:38.625
Smile.

00:59:39.250 --> 00:59:40.208
Mom.

00:59:40.291 --> 00:59:42.916
-[chuckles]
-What happened?

00:59:43.791 --> 00:59:46.958
First of all, there's a huge age gap.

00:59:47.041 --> 00:59:50.791
Secondly, the photo Aunt Ina sent me

00:59:50.875 --> 00:59:53.875
was from ten years ago.
[exclaims quietly]

00:59:53.958 --> 00:59:55.750
So it's a no?

00:59:55.833 --> 00:59:56.833
Of course not.

00:59:56.916 --> 00:59:58.000
No way.

00:59:58.625 --> 00:59:59.416
Why?

00:59:59.500 --> 01:00:00.875
You're being reckless.

01:00:00.958 --> 01:00:01.750
What?

01:00:01.833 --> 01:00:04.666
You think it doesn't bother us that
you haven't found someone?

01:00:05.333 --> 01:00:06.916
All you care about is yourself.

01:00:07.750 --> 01:00:09.083
Why me?

01:00:09.166 --> 01:00:12.166
Karin's mad that
we haven't done the invitations

01:00:13.208 --> 01:00:14.583
and the prewedding photos.

01:00:16.583 --> 01:00:18.583
Then you go and say something like that?

01:00:18.666 --> 01:00:20.083
It's not my fault.

01:00:20.791 --> 01:00:23.000
I did what Dad wanted.

01:00:23.083 --> 01:00:26.875
He told me to just meet her,
not that it had to work out.

01:00:27.541 --> 01:00:28.791
You still blame me?

01:00:28.875 --> 01:00:30.958
Go ahead and take prewedding photos.

01:00:31.041 --> 01:00:32.125
Don't wait for me.

01:00:32.208 --> 01:00:35.250
That's enough.

01:00:35.333 --> 01:00:36.791
-You too, Ahmad.
-Huh?

01:00:36.875 --> 01:00:39.125
Do your own thing. Don't wait for anyone.

01:00:39.208 --> 01:00:42.125
Why take it out on me? I've been quiet.

01:00:42.208 --> 01:00:44.833
Because everything here is my fault.

01:00:46.125 --> 01:00:47.791
No one's blaming you.

01:00:47.875 --> 01:00:48.875
[sighs]

01:00:50.958 --> 01:00:54.666
How could you speak like that
to your brother?

01:00:55.291 --> 01:00:57.000
You were out of line.

01:00:59.083 --> 01:01:01.250
Mom, I didn't say anything.

01:01:01.333 --> 01:01:03.125
[Asha] My Dad is nagging me.

01:01:03.708 --> 01:01:05.583
There's not much time left.

01:01:05.666 --> 01:01:07.750
We have to send the invitations.

01:01:07.833 --> 01:01:10.083
[somber music]

01:01:23.666 --> 01:01:25.375
[sighs]

01:01:30.916 --> 01:01:38.875
HI RIFA, HOW ARE YOU?

01:01:41.833 --> 01:01:44.958
[phone buzzing]

01:01:56.333 --> 01:01:57.625
[Nisa] Fadly.

01:01:58.750 --> 01:02:00.500
I miss you.

01:02:00.583 --> 01:02:03.416
I didn't want to be in this position.

01:02:03.500 --> 01:02:06.375
Can you stop contacting me?

01:02:06.458 --> 01:02:08.625
Your brother came to my studio
the other day.

01:02:09.083 --> 01:02:12.333
[sniffles] I'm sorry.

01:02:12.416 --> 01:02:14.750
I told him to stay away from you.

01:02:15.958 --> 01:02:18.041
Let's meet up and talk.

01:02:18.125 --> 01:02:19.708
You can say it now.

01:02:20.250 --> 01:02:22.041
I have to see you.

01:02:22.833 --> 01:02:24.166
It won't take long.

01:02:25.666 --> 01:02:27.541
I'll go to Makassar tomorrow.

01:02:27.625 --> 01:02:29.541
[sighs]

01:02:29.625 --> 01:02:32.916
[somber music]

01:02:50.500 --> 01:02:51.875
I've missed you.

01:02:55.166 --> 01:02:56.583
What do you want to say?

01:03:00.833 --> 01:03:02.125
I can't stay long.

01:03:04.750 --> 01:03:06.583
Take me away, Fadly.

01:03:06.666 --> 01:03:08.041
[deep breaths]

01:03:11.083 --> 01:03:12.250
What can I do?

01:03:16.500 --> 01:03:19.083
We don't know if we don't try.

01:03:20.125 --> 01:03:21.375
It's too late, Nisa.

01:03:21.458 --> 01:03:22.875
No, Fadly.

01:03:23.458 --> 01:03:24.916
It's not too late.

01:03:25.625 --> 01:03:29.041
I admit I was wrong,
but it's not my fault.

01:03:29.125 --> 01:03:31.000
I want to fight for us.

01:03:31.625 --> 01:03:33.333
I won't give up easily.

01:03:33.416 --> 01:03:34.833
We can't.

01:03:36.958 --> 01:03:39.500
Doing that will just enrage our families.

01:03:43.750 --> 01:03:45.291
Why are you being a coward?

01:03:46.708 --> 01:03:47.750
Is this it?

01:03:49.083 --> 01:03:50.250
You call this love?

01:03:51.125 --> 01:03:54.250
You won't even fight for our relationship.

01:03:57.083 --> 01:03:59.458
So the past three years
mean nothing to you?

01:04:03.500 --> 01:04:05.291
Maybe the saying is true.

01:04:07.083 --> 01:04:09.750
Being together a long time
doesn't mean true love.

01:04:11.208 --> 01:04:13.583
[somber music]

01:04:20.250 --> 01:04:22.416
Is it really love
if you don't fight for it?

01:04:27.500 --> 01:04:29.458
You're not a real man.

01:04:31.208 --> 01:04:32.458
[Nisa sighs]

01:04:48.041 --> 01:04:50.958
[sings lines of sad love song teasingly]

01:05:00.750 --> 01:05:01.833
It's not like that, sir.

01:05:02.791 --> 01:05:05.000
My mind's a bit blank right now.

01:05:06.166 --> 01:05:08.541
I can't come up with anything for a song.

01:05:13.833 --> 01:05:15.083
Look at that.

01:05:18.125 --> 01:05:20.708
Falling in love is a choice, Fadly.

01:05:22.583 --> 01:05:24.708
But it's not just about choosing,

01:05:25.333 --> 01:05:29.375
it's about the responsibility
that comes with it.

01:05:31.875 --> 01:05:33.625
God's plan

01:05:34.500 --> 01:05:35.875
is never wrong.

01:05:38.291 --> 01:05:40.958
What disappoints us

01:05:41.041 --> 01:05:44.500
isn't the wrong choice,

01:05:45.000 --> 01:05:48.208
but our late realization
of the purpose behind it.

01:05:50.125 --> 01:05:52.708
[solemn music]

01:05:56.083 --> 01:05:59.166
Love enters through the eyes
and settles in the heart.

01:05:59.250 --> 01:06:00.291
[knocking]

01:06:00.375 --> 01:06:02.666
[video continues indistinctly]

01:06:02.750 --> 01:06:04.000
Come in.

01:06:07.833 --> 01:06:09.333
Here's your drink.

01:06:09.416 --> 01:06:11.583
-Okay, thank you.
-No problem.

01:06:14.166 --> 01:06:15.000
Aunty.

01:06:15.708 --> 01:06:17.041
Where are you going?

01:06:17.125 --> 01:06:18.291
The kitchen.

01:06:18.375 --> 01:06:22.125
No, stay here with me. I'm bored.

01:06:22.208 --> 01:06:24.333
[chuckles] Oh, sure.

01:06:25.625 --> 01:06:26.791
Come here.

01:06:26.875 --> 01:06:28.958
Don't just stand there, come here.

01:06:30.000 --> 01:06:31.125
Excuse me.

01:06:31.208 --> 01:06:33.208
It's okay. Sit here.

01:06:33.291 --> 01:06:35.166
[laughing]

01:06:37.125 --> 01:06:38.625
That's hilarious.

01:06:39.833 --> 01:06:42.375
Don't feel "insesoh."

01:06:43.541 --> 01:06:46.041
It should've been "insechure."

01:06:46.791 --> 01:06:47.625
Insecure?

01:06:47.708 --> 01:06:49.083
Insecure.

01:06:49.166 --> 01:06:52.291
You know your English well.

01:06:52.375 --> 01:06:54.000
[laughing]

01:06:56.541 --> 01:06:58.083
Oops.

01:06:58.166 --> 01:06:59.375
I got carried away.

01:06:59.458 --> 01:07:00.625
It's okay.

01:07:00.708 --> 01:07:01.916
[in thick accent] I lost control.

01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:04.250
[laughing]

01:07:05.000 --> 01:07:05.875
It's good.

01:07:05.958 --> 01:07:07.250
[man on video speaking]

01:07:07.333 --> 01:07:09.791
-Look at this. It's viral.
-Yeah.

01:07:09.875 --> 01:07:14.541
This guy blew up online.
It's getting millions of views.

01:07:15.291 --> 01:07:18.250
…because the dowry was crazy expensive.

01:07:18.333 --> 01:07:20.791
She was an only child of a rich family.

01:07:20.875 --> 01:07:24.125
It makes sense
why the dowry was that much.

01:07:24.208 --> 01:07:26.083
It was one…

01:07:26.166 --> 01:07:27.916
One billion, not a million.

01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:29.625
-One billion.
-One billion.

01:07:29.708 --> 01:07:31.208
-Aunty.
-Yes?

01:07:32.208 --> 01:07:33.791
What about me?

01:07:34.666 --> 01:07:36.333
As for you…

01:07:36.416 --> 01:07:39.666
You have a master's degree,
have undertaken Umrah,

01:07:39.750 --> 01:07:44.208
and are an only child
inheriting your father's housing business.

01:07:44.291 --> 01:07:45.708
[exclaims]

01:07:45.791 --> 01:07:47.625
Your dowry should be
at least three billion.

01:07:47.708 --> 01:07:49.291
What? Three billion?

01:07:49.375 --> 01:07:50.125
That's too expensive.

01:07:50.208 --> 01:07:52.458
But that price is reasonable.

01:07:52.541 --> 01:07:55.250
Imagine a football player. You know Messi?

01:07:55.333 --> 01:07:58.125
Do you think he'd be paid
with Ngawi's minimum wage?

01:07:58.208 --> 01:07:59.250
Definitely not.

01:07:59.333 --> 01:08:00.583
I guess so.

01:08:00.666 --> 01:08:03.541
Unless Messi is okay with that pay.

01:08:03.625 --> 01:08:05.750
That's another story.

01:08:09.250 --> 01:08:12.166
I never noticed how much you know.

01:08:12.250 --> 01:08:14.750
From football to minimum wage.

01:08:14.833 --> 01:08:15.750
[chuckles]

01:08:15.833 --> 01:08:17.875
I don't mean to brag,

01:08:17.958 --> 01:08:20.916
but this is just who I am.

01:08:21.458 --> 01:08:22.625
[chuckles]

01:08:22.708 --> 01:08:26.916
Even though I'm from the countryside,
we must always stay informed.

01:08:27.458 --> 01:08:29.000
Especially about mental health.

01:08:29.083 --> 01:08:29.916
[chuckles]

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:33.416
It's important. Programs on TV say so too.

01:08:34.625 --> 01:08:37.708
I have some advice for you

01:08:37.791 --> 01:08:39.291
about finding a partner.

01:08:40.416 --> 01:08:41.500
Don't take it the wrong way,

01:08:41.583 --> 01:08:43.583
but in my opinion…

01:08:43.666 --> 01:08:47.041
What's the South Jakarta slang for it?

01:08:47.125 --> 01:08:49.208
Don't be too picky.

01:08:49.708 --> 01:08:53.208
Just make sure the guy
isn't full of red flags.

01:08:53.291 --> 01:08:57.291
Just choose one. Otherwise,
it'll be hard to find a match.

01:08:57.375 --> 01:09:01.583
As for me, I'd accept whoever comes along.

01:09:01.666 --> 01:09:03.041
But the problem is, no one's coming.

01:09:03.125 --> 01:09:03.916
[Karin's mom] Dear.

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:04.958
Yes, Mom?

01:09:05.875 --> 01:09:08.000
What about the invitation?

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:12.416
Are they going to be ready to go

01:09:12.500 --> 01:09:15.833
before your prewedding trip to Makassar?

01:09:15.916 --> 01:09:20.791
The neighbors and our family
keep asking about it.

01:09:22.041 --> 01:09:23.375
[Asha] Babe.

01:09:23.458 --> 01:09:26.666
When can we send the invitations?

01:09:29.625 --> 01:09:32.041
Just wait, babe. Be patient.

01:09:33.625 --> 01:09:35.000
Let's wait

01:09:35.750 --> 01:09:38.583
for Fadly to find someone new.

01:09:38.666 --> 01:09:40.166
When will that be?

01:09:40.250 --> 01:09:42.541
My parents keep asking about it.

01:09:43.166 --> 01:09:44.250
[somber music]

01:09:44.333 --> 01:09:46.208
Do you want to cancel the wedding?

01:09:48.750 --> 01:09:50.625
Fadly, have you decided?

01:09:51.916 --> 01:09:53.000
Yeah.

01:09:53.083 --> 01:09:55.375
My future in-laws won't stop asking,

01:09:55.875 --> 01:09:57.333
and I'm out of excuses.

01:09:59.041 --> 01:10:00.416
You don't seem worried.

01:10:03.708 --> 01:10:04.916
Just wait.

01:10:05.666 --> 01:10:07.291
[heavy sigh]

01:10:07.375 --> 01:10:08.666
Until when?

01:10:12.125 --> 01:10:15.000
Why didn't you accept the match
Mom set up?

01:10:16.416 --> 01:10:18.666
Just pick someone already.

01:10:19.500 --> 01:10:20.916
Don't let your indecision

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:22.958
ruin your brothers' chances
to get married.

01:10:25.625 --> 01:10:27.250
Are you blaming me?

01:10:27.875 --> 01:10:29.166
You think I wanted this?

01:10:30.000 --> 01:10:30.833
Huh?

01:10:32.125 --> 01:10:35.000
You think you can handle my situation?

01:10:35.500 --> 01:10:36.833
It's clearly your fault.

01:10:37.916 --> 01:10:41.583
Why'd you say yes to Dad
if Nisa wasn't available?

01:10:41.666 --> 01:10:43.541
Why are you putting this on me, Ahmad?

01:10:43.625 --> 01:10:45.250
Why don't you blame Dad?

01:10:45.958 --> 01:10:47.833
He's the one who wanted
a joint wedding, not me!

01:10:48.500 --> 01:10:50.375
-Fadly watch your mouth.
-Hey.

01:10:50.458 --> 01:10:51.291
Ahmad.

01:10:51.375 --> 01:10:52.750
-You want to blame Dad?
-Ahmad.

01:10:53.208 --> 01:10:54.416
What?

01:10:55.125 --> 01:10:56.208
You're taking his side now?

01:10:58.000 --> 01:10:59.541
You want to call off the wedding?

01:11:00.166 --> 01:11:02.208
You think this isn't bothering me too?

01:11:02.583 --> 01:11:04.083
This affects all of us.

01:11:04.583 --> 01:11:05.750
Listen.

01:11:06.458 --> 01:11:09.333
If one of us backs out, we all go down.

01:11:10.166 --> 01:11:11.416
Go ahead, I don't want to.

01:11:11.500 --> 01:11:14.166
-You're so selfish, Ahmad.
-What did you say?

01:11:14.250 --> 01:11:16.333
-Watch your mouth.
-Go on, hit me!

01:11:17.875 --> 01:11:19.416
Fadly, you'd better go.

01:11:22.125 --> 01:11:24.208
I have to take care of my wedding,

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:26.416
and now him?

01:11:31.416 --> 01:11:33.583
I'm sure he's trying his best.

01:11:33.666 --> 01:11:36.208
But it can't be helped
if he hasn't found his soulmate.

01:11:36.291 --> 01:11:38.416
We can't just wait around.

01:11:38.500 --> 01:11:40.250
We're out of time.

01:11:43.166 --> 01:11:44.916
I understand.

01:11:45.000 --> 01:11:48.833
You, me, and Fadly,
we all hate this situation.

01:11:49.583 --> 01:11:50.666
Ahmad.

01:11:52.375 --> 01:11:54.291
We have to support Fadly.

01:11:56.166 --> 01:11:57.250
[sighs]

01:11:57.958 --> 01:12:01.458
Rifa, what about your PhD?

01:12:01.541 --> 01:12:03.083
Which university?

01:12:07.541 --> 01:12:09.666
I'm good, Mom.

01:12:12.875 --> 01:12:13.708
Huh?

01:12:14.083 --> 01:12:18.708
Many of your friends
chose to study abroad.

01:12:18.791 --> 01:12:20.416
Are you not going?

01:12:20.833 --> 01:12:23.625
We don't have to do everything others do.

01:12:25.125 --> 01:12:27.916
She doesn't want her dowry to cost more.

01:12:28.000 --> 01:12:29.333
[Rifa's mom] Surti.

01:12:29.416 --> 01:12:32.958
My daughter's dowry
should be three billion.

01:12:33.041 --> 01:12:35.000
[Surti] Oops.
I didn't mean to drink yours.

01:12:35.083 --> 01:12:37.625
I think I need some healing.

01:12:37.708 --> 01:12:40.166
Wait, I'll get you a new one.

01:12:42.583 --> 01:12:45.416
You're coming with me
to Aunty Rika's, right?

01:12:46.250 --> 01:12:48.500
All your aunts will be there.

01:12:48.583 --> 01:12:49.833
I'd rather not.

01:12:50.625 --> 01:12:52.875
They'll bombard me with questions.

01:12:53.541 --> 01:12:56.333
When am I getting married,
why don't I have a boyfriend,

01:12:56.416 --> 01:12:59.541
why don't I like this guy or that guy…

01:13:01.625 --> 01:13:02.916
Okay.

01:13:04.083 --> 01:13:06.708
You don't have to come.

01:13:07.791 --> 01:13:09.000
[Rifa's mom laughs softly]

01:13:14.500 --> 01:13:15.750
[sighs]

01:13:22.708 --> 01:13:24.166
Puang.

01:13:24.250 --> 01:13:26.791
Don't be too picky.

01:13:26.875 --> 01:13:28.750
[solemn music]

01:13:30.250 --> 01:13:31.375
[exhales]

01:13:40.791 --> 01:13:43.416
Stay calm, Fadly.

01:13:44.458 --> 01:13:46.458
Your soulmate is in God's hands.

01:13:48.500 --> 01:13:50.041
It's all about timing.

01:13:51.166 --> 01:13:52.791
It's all about timing.

01:13:54.416 --> 01:13:55.541
It's all about timing.

01:13:55.625 --> 01:13:57.791
[phone buzzing]

01:13:59.125 --> 01:14:00.125
Hello, brother?

01:14:00.208 --> 01:14:03.375
[Ariping] Let's go to Malino.
Kallang's concert's on.

01:14:03.458 --> 01:14:05.208
When? Right now?

01:14:05.291 --> 01:14:07.750
Yeah, now. Come on, pick me up.

01:14:08.708 --> 01:14:09.750
Okay.

01:14:10.458 --> 01:14:11.750
-Wait for me.
-Will do.

01:14:13.416 --> 01:14:15.083
It's all about timing.

01:14:15.166 --> 01:14:17.958
[bright music]

01:14:34.250 --> 01:14:36.000
-Ahmad.
-Mm?

01:14:36.083 --> 01:14:37.416
Try to come up with another excuse.

01:14:37.500 --> 01:14:38.750
[scoffs]

01:14:39.375 --> 01:14:41.083
I'm out of ideas.

01:14:42.708 --> 01:14:44.333
How about

01:14:44.416 --> 01:14:45.791
the printing house burned down?

01:14:46.333 --> 01:14:47.708
That was last week.

01:14:49.083 --> 01:14:52.666
The printing guy is busy
printing his own wedding invitations.

01:14:52.750 --> 01:14:53.875
Three days ago.

01:14:55.166 --> 01:14:57.333
The printer guy is doing Hajj?

01:14:57.416 --> 01:14:58.958
Great idea.

01:14:59.041 --> 01:15:00.416
It's not time for Hajj.

01:15:00.500 --> 01:15:02.250
-Going hiking?
-Hiking?

01:15:03.000 --> 01:15:04.166
I guess.

01:15:04.250 --> 01:15:05.500
I'll try.

01:15:15.708 --> 01:15:17.333
[exclaims]

01:15:17.916 --> 01:15:19.166
So hardworking.

01:15:20.291 --> 01:15:21.541
Don't forget mine too.

01:15:25.958 --> 01:15:27.625
What's with your brother?

01:15:27.708 --> 01:15:28.750
He's yours too.

01:15:30.375 --> 01:15:31.791
Maybe he's found the one.

01:15:31.875 --> 01:15:33.791
Really? You can tell?

01:15:34.250 --> 01:15:37.750
That's the smile of someone in love.

01:15:37.833 --> 01:15:39.166
It's different?

01:15:39.250 --> 01:15:40.458
It is.

01:15:40.541 --> 01:15:43.916
The smile of someone
getting a lot of money?

01:15:46.500 --> 01:15:48.416
Smile of someone hitting a target?

01:15:49.916 --> 01:15:51.416
I knew it.

01:15:51.500 --> 01:15:52.750
It looks the same.

01:15:52.833 --> 01:15:54.291
It is.

01:15:55.375 --> 01:15:57.125
Hitting a target earns you money.

01:15:57.208 --> 01:15:59.333
It's all about the money!

01:15:59.791 --> 01:16:00.833
Right.

01:16:00.916 --> 01:16:03.083
[energetic music]

01:16:07.625 --> 01:16:10.000
If I tidy up my appearance,

01:16:11.416 --> 01:16:12.958
I will look cool.

01:16:13.583 --> 01:16:14.625
All of this

01:16:15.583 --> 01:16:17.250
by the grace of God.

01:16:18.875 --> 01:16:21.750
[energetic music continues]

01:16:32.458 --> 01:16:34.083
It's all about timing.

01:16:36.375 --> 01:16:40.458
[whispering] It's all about timing.

01:16:41.125 --> 01:16:42.958
[engine revs]

01:16:43.041 --> 01:16:44.666
It's all about timing.

01:16:48.208 --> 01:16:50.333
What kind of smile is that?

01:16:51.875 --> 01:16:54.083
A brand-new-jacket smile.

01:16:58.166 --> 01:16:59.208
What took you so long?

01:16:59.291 --> 01:17:01.000
Easy, there.

01:17:02.083 --> 01:17:02.833
Hold my bag.

01:17:02.916 --> 01:17:04.500
So demanding.

01:17:06.791 --> 01:17:08.750
Wait, stop. I need to pee.

01:17:12.125 --> 01:17:15.083
[phone buzzing]

01:17:18.041 --> 01:17:19.083
Rifa?

01:17:21.458 --> 01:17:22.500
Hello?

01:17:24.041 --> 01:17:26.000
Huh? Right now?

01:17:27.041 --> 01:17:28.000
I'm on my way.

01:17:29.083 --> 01:17:30.208
Wait for me.

01:17:33.458 --> 01:17:34.333
Fadly!

01:17:39.416 --> 01:17:40.416
Fad.

01:17:40.500 --> 01:17:41.791
-Hey.
-Hi.

01:17:41.875 --> 01:17:44.416
In the Name of God,
Most Gracious, Most Merciful.

01:17:45.750 --> 01:17:46.958
-Hi.
-Hi.

01:17:50.208 --> 01:17:52.291
Sorry for keeping you waiting.

01:17:52.375 --> 01:17:53.625
Not at all.

01:17:57.333 --> 01:17:58.458
How are you?

01:17:58.958 --> 01:18:00.416
I'm good. You?

01:18:03.291 --> 01:18:04.583
[mumbles]

01:18:05.791 --> 01:18:06.958
What, Fad?

01:18:12.291 --> 01:18:13.250
Rifa.

01:18:15.541 --> 01:18:16.750
I want to propose to you.

01:18:19.000 --> 01:18:19.875
Fadly.

01:18:23.083 --> 01:18:23.916
Nisa?

01:18:25.250 --> 01:18:26.083
Oh.

01:18:27.083 --> 01:18:30.125
Is this the reason you won't fight for us?

01:18:30.208 --> 01:18:32.833
Huh? Fight for what?

01:18:33.666 --> 01:18:35.625
Nisa, enough.

01:18:35.708 --> 01:18:37.416
Stop bothering me.

01:18:37.500 --> 01:18:38.666
We're done.

01:18:38.750 --> 01:18:41.458
Fadly, I'm sorry.

01:18:41.541 --> 01:18:44.791
I admit I was wrong,
but we can find a solution together.

01:18:44.875 --> 01:18:46.916
What else do you want? Stop this.

01:18:47.000 --> 01:18:48.958
-It's not even my wish.
-Sorry, this is too much.

01:18:49.041 --> 01:18:50.208
Sorry, who are you?

01:18:50.916 --> 01:18:51.958
Stay out of this.

01:18:52.041 --> 01:18:53.125
Who are you?

01:18:53.208 --> 01:18:54.625
I was talking to Fadly.

01:18:54.708 --> 01:18:55.875
So she's the reason?

01:18:55.958 --> 01:18:57.125
What reason?

01:18:57.916 --> 01:18:58.958
You never told me about her.

01:18:59.041 --> 01:19:01.875
Didn't I tell you to stop contacting Nisa?

01:19:02.625 --> 01:19:03.625
And you too, Nisa.

01:19:03.708 --> 01:19:05.833
You're about to get married,
but you're still wandering around?

01:19:05.916 --> 01:19:09.166
Please, can you stop yelling?

01:19:09.583 --> 01:19:10.875
Who are you?

01:19:11.833 --> 01:19:13.333
I'm Fadly's girlfriend.

01:19:13.958 --> 01:19:17.208
You're causing trouble,
and it's bothering us.

01:19:17.291 --> 01:19:18.416
Stay out of this.

01:19:18.500 --> 01:19:19.750
Just watch your boyfriend.

01:19:19.833 --> 01:19:23.208
Hey! You can mess with me,
but leave my girl alone.

01:19:24.083 --> 01:19:25.041
What?!

01:19:26.291 --> 01:19:27.458
[Nisa's brother grunts]

01:19:42.041 --> 01:19:43.000
Let's sit down.

01:20:03.291 --> 01:20:04.291
-Sorry.
-Sorry.

01:20:05.375 --> 01:20:06.291
I'm sorry.

01:20:08.666 --> 01:20:09.541
Me too.

01:20:10.166 --> 01:20:11.833
I should be apologizing.

01:20:14.375 --> 01:20:15.500
Sorry

01:20:16.708 --> 01:20:19.416
you got caught up in that mess.

01:20:21.500 --> 01:20:26.000
I'm sorry for pretending
to be your girlfriend.

01:20:26.541 --> 01:20:28.041
I felt bad.

01:20:35.125 --> 01:20:37.333
I'd like to apologize for one more thing.

01:20:37.416 --> 01:20:38.375
What?

01:20:42.083 --> 01:20:44.875
I'm sorry I've been

01:20:46.458 --> 01:20:48.041
a coward all this time.

01:20:52.166 --> 01:20:56.208
I was scared of the gap
in our social station,

01:20:58.000 --> 01:21:02.583
so I wasn't honest with myself.

01:21:04.583 --> 01:21:06.333
You're not saying this…

01:21:09.000 --> 01:21:11.500
just to use me as a rebound, right?

01:21:11.583 --> 01:21:14.250
Of course not. I swear to God.

01:21:14.916 --> 01:21:16.041
I promise,

01:21:16.916 --> 01:21:19.208
this isn't like that.

01:21:21.500 --> 01:21:24.250
This time, it's about me.

01:21:27.083 --> 01:21:29.916
I won't make the same mistake again.

01:21:35.833 --> 01:21:37.416
I'll think about it.

01:21:38.708 --> 01:21:41.166
[gentle music]

01:21:45.125 --> 01:21:46.291
-Fadly.
-Mm?

01:21:46.375 --> 01:21:47.375
Let's go home.

01:21:48.041 --> 01:21:49.083
Huh?

01:21:51.625 --> 01:21:52.541
Go home.

01:21:52.625 --> 01:21:55.000
Oh, okay. Let me pay for that.

01:21:55.833 --> 01:21:56.958
Wait.

01:21:58.291 --> 01:21:59.333
[sighs]

01:22:06.458 --> 01:22:07.791
Good evening.

01:22:07.875 --> 01:22:10.458
What's the bill for that table?

01:22:12.791 --> 01:22:14.750
120,000.

01:22:14.833 --> 01:22:16.125
120,000?

01:22:18.125 --> 01:22:20.291
[witty music]

01:22:25.791 --> 01:22:26.833
Rifa.

01:22:29.375 --> 01:22:31.125
I need a favor just this once.

01:22:31.875 --> 01:22:32.708
What?

01:22:32.791 --> 01:22:36.291
They only take cash,
but I don't have my wallet.

01:22:36.375 --> 01:22:37.958
I left my wallet in my bag…

01:22:38.041 --> 01:22:39.500
-My bag is with…
-It's fine.

01:22:41.250 --> 01:22:43.958
But I didn't mean to…

01:22:44.041 --> 01:22:45.875
-It's okay.
-Doesn't mean I can't afford it.

01:22:45.958 --> 01:22:47.750
Yes, I believe you.

01:22:51.291 --> 01:22:52.583
Do you bring your car?

01:22:53.166 --> 01:22:54.250
No.

01:22:54.916 --> 01:22:57.750
If so, I can drop you off.

01:23:00.875 --> 01:23:01.958
I'm good.

01:23:02.416 --> 01:23:04.250
-Let me take you.
-I'm good.

01:23:04.333 --> 01:23:06.625
It's too dangerous at night.

01:23:07.500 --> 01:23:08.625
Let me take you.

01:23:11.375 --> 01:23:12.750
It's okay, come on.

01:23:13.833 --> 01:23:17.041
["Seberapa Pantas" by Sheila on 7 playing]

01:23:22.875 --> 01:23:24.458
[no audible dialog]

01:23:43.000 --> 01:23:44.125
What's wrong?

01:23:45.833 --> 01:23:46.958
I'm out of gas.

01:23:47.500 --> 01:23:48.458
Oh.

01:23:48.541 --> 01:23:50.625
Okay. Should we push?

01:23:52.208 --> 01:23:53.500
[groans]

01:23:53.583 --> 01:23:55.041
Sorry, Rifa.

01:23:55.875 --> 01:23:58.791
-Such an embarrassment.
-Don't worry about it.

01:24:01.000 --> 01:24:02.750
Why blame the motorcycle?

01:24:03.750 --> 01:24:05.625
Show it some love.

01:24:05.708 --> 01:24:08.375
Thanks to it, we can stay together longer.

01:24:12.541 --> 01:24:13.666
[chuckles]

01:24:15.666 --> 01:24:16.625
Sorry.

01:24:16.708 --> 01:24:17.875
It's fine.

01:24:18.708 --> 01:24:23.000
There's a gas station ahead.

01:24:24.000 --> 01:24:25.208
How did you know?

01:24:25.291 --> 01:24:26.208
I know.

01:24:26.291 --> 01:24:27.666
[laughs]

01:24:32.416 --> 01:24:34.000
[Fatimah] What do we do?

01:24:34.083 --> 01:24:36.333
It's almost time.

01:24:36.416 --> 01:24:37.583
[Ahmad] Yeah, Dad.

01:24:37.666 --> 01:24:40.541
Because of Fadly,
things are falling apart.

01:24:40.625 --> 01:24:43.958
He won't agree to an arranged match,
and hasn't found anyone himself.

01:24:44.041 --> 01:24:48.541
[Fatimah] Ahmad. You shouldn't say that
about your brother.

01:24:48.625 --> 01:24:50.333
Can't you see how hard he's trying?

01:24:55.208 --> 01:24:56.375
Dear,

01:24:57.375 --> 01:24:59.000
what if

01:25:00.500 --> 01:25:02.208
this joint wedding

01:25:02.291 --> 01:25:06.458
will just be for Kifly and Ahmad?

01:25:06.541 --> 01:25:08.208
[Mustafa] No, dear.

01:25:08.291 --> 01:25:10.541
I'd lose face and be humiliated.

01:25:10.625 --> 01:25:14.916
Especially in front of Karin
and Asha's families.

01:25:16.041 --> 01:25:18.416
And as his father…

01:25:21.500 --> 01:25:26.125
I'd be ashamed if Fadly can't
share the joy on that day.

01:25:26.958 --> 01:25:29.208
How could I call myself a father?

01:25:31.833 --> 01:25:33.666
Ever since he was small,

01:25:33.750 --> 01:25:36.750
Fadly has had it rough.

01:25:36.833 --> 01:25:42.041
You know I'm just a teacher.

01:25:43.000 --> 01:25:45.541
It was your decision

01:25:45.625 --> 01:25:48.666
that we should wait to have another baby.

01:25:49.458 --> 01:25:53.208
I regret not following your advice.

01:25:55.250 --> 01:25:57.791
Fadly, our eldest,

01:25:59.333 --> 01:26:02.958
has never had a taste of happiness.

01:26:05.541 --> 01:26:09.166
[Mustafa] It would break my heart

01:26:11.791 --> 01:26:14.625
if his younger siblings got married

01:26:15.583 --> 01:26:17.541
before he did.

01:26:27.791 --> 01:26:28.833
Sorry, Dad.

01:26:29.708 --> 01:26:31.333
But…

01:26:34.500 --> 01:26:36.458
wouldn't your honor be at stake as well

01:26:36.541 --> 01:26:39.583
if Kifly's and my wedding is canceled?

01:26:39.666 --> 01:26:40.625
Ahmad.

01:26:41.291 --> 01:26:43.291
What's really going on

01:26:44.375 --> 01:26:46.958
between you and your brother?

01:26:47.041 --> 01:26:47.833
Hm?

01:26:48.250 --> 01:26:49.625
There's nothing wrong.

01:26:52.958 --> 01:26:54.125
I just

01:26:56.000 --> 01:26:57.083
want to find a way…

01:26:57.166 --> 01:26:59.041
That's not the right way!

01:26:59.833 --> 01:27:01.708
You're talking nonsense.

01:27:01.791 --> 01:27:03.375
It's not like that, Mom.

01:27:04.208 --> 01:27:06.875
[Fatimah] Stop blaming your brother.

01:27:08.291 --> 01:27:10.083
He's testing my patience.

01:27:16.166 --> 01:27:17.291
Dad.

01:27:18.041 --> 01:27:19.041
It's okay, Dad.

01:27:19.125 --> 01:27:20.416
You're home.

01:27:25.750 --> 01:27:27.416
Don't stress it.

01:27:29.666 --> 01:27:31.083
[sighs]

01:27:32.541 --> 01:27:33.958
I've found someone.

01:27:34.041 --> 01:27:35.458
Oh my God.

01:27:36.083 --> 01:27:37.208
Who?

01:27:37.291 --> 01:27:39.583
Remember my friend in college?

01:27:40.583 --> 01:27:41.541
Rifa.

01:27:41.625 --> 01:27:43.458
-Rifa.
-Yes.

01:27:43.541 --> 01:27:46.083
Rifa? The daughter of that rich man?

01:27:46.166 --> 01:27:47.375
Yes.

01:27:47.458 --> 01:27:48.708
No.

01:27:48.791 --> 01:27:49.875
Dear…

01:27:49.958 --> 01:27:52.875
I can never afford her dowry.

01:27:52.958 --> 01:27:54.125
-No.
-Dear.

01:27:54.208 --> 01:27:55.541
Dad.

01:27:56.833 --> 01:27:58.375
Come on.

01:27:59.916 --> 01:28:02.958
Now that I've found someone, you refuse?

01:28:03.500 --> 01:28:05.958
[Ahmad] Fadly.
Didn't you hear what Dad said?

01:28:06.041 --> 01:28:07.083
Ahmad.

01:28:08.125 --> 01:28:10.125
Let's just move forward first.

01:28:10.500 --> 01:28:12.208
If our hearts are in the right place,

01:28:13.500 --> 01:28:15.416
and Rifa is meant for me,

01:28:16.583 --> 01:28:18.666
God willing, it will all work out.

01:28:19.916 --> 01:28:21.083
Right, Mom?

01:28:21.666 --> 01:28:23.208
God willing.

01:28:23.291 --> 01:28:25.125
It's all about timing.

01:28:26.208 --> 01:28:27.333
Yes.

01:28:29.375 --> 01:28:30.208
But…

01:28:30.708 --> 01:28:32.041
What?

01:28:33.625 --> 01:28:34.500
She hasn't replied.

01:28:34.583 --> 01:28:35.750
What?

01:28:36.416 --> 01:28:38.041
-I hope she said yes.
-What do we do?

01:28:39.500 --> 01:28:43.333
I've brought up the marriage proposal,

01:28:44.291 --> 01:28:46.166
but she hasn't given me a reply.

01:28:47.083 --> 01:28:48.625
[Fadly] I have a friend from college.

01:28:48.708 --> 01:28:50.083
Her name is Rifa.

01:28:51.541 --> 01:28:53.666
I had feelings for her,

01:28:53.750 --> 01:28:55.750
and I tried to reconnect with her.

01:28:56.250 --> 01:28:57.208
But

01:28:58.333 --> 01:29:00.500
since we're out of time,

01:29:01.875 --> 01:29:05.583
I explained my circumstances
and intentions.

01:29:05.666 --> 01:29:07.208
And?

01:29:07.291 --> 01:29:10.083
She still hasn't said anything.

01:29:12.375 --> 01:29:13.583
Maybe I should call her.

01:29:13.666 --> 01:29:15.250
-Hey.
-Get a clear answer.

01:29:15.333 --> 01:29:17.041
That's enough.

01:29:19.000 --> 01:29:20.458
You've done your part.

01:29:21.166 --> 01:29:23.708
Now the universe decides.

01:29:24.875 --> 01:29:27.208
If it's meant to be,

01:29:27.291 --> 01:29:29.333
then you will be together.

01:29:31.041 --> 01:29:34.541
[cheerful music]

01:29:34.625 --> 01:29:37.291
Thank you. Here it is.

01:29:37.375 --> 01:29:40.041
Okay, look that way.

01:29:40.125 --> 01:29:42.375
-Look here.
-[camera shutter clicks]

01:29:43.791 --> 01:29:45.291
[indistinct chatter]

01:29:45.375 --> 01:29:46.500
Here it is.

01:29:48.583 --> 01:29:51.416
[man] I've never seen
a three-in-one wedding before.

01:29:51.500 --> 01:29:54.541
Someone requested a five-in-one,
but I declined.

01:29:54.625 --> 01:29:55.833
The stage couldn't fit them all.

01:29:55.916 --> 01:30:00.166
10 couples, add their parents, that's 20.

01:30:00.250 --> 01:30:02.916
And with the bridesmaids,
that's 30 people!

01:30:03.000 --> 01:30:04.625
[laughing]

01:30:04.708 --> 01:30:06.375
[camera shutter clicks]

01:30:09.250 --> 01:30:11.041
You're still on dating apps?

01:30:11.708 --> 01:30:14.125
Huh? It's too late.

01:30:14.208 --> 01:30:15.541
The wedding is in two weeks.

01:30:16.541 --> 01:30:17.375
Gosh.

01:30:17.458 --> 01:30:19.416
[phone buzzing]

01:30:23.375 --> 01:30:24.333
Hello.

01:30:25.250 --> 01:30:26.250
Now?

01:30:27.833 --> 01:30:30.416
Yes, I can go. Where?

01:30:40.666 --> 01:30:41.750
[car door shuts]

01:30:43.416 --> 01:30:44.375
Nisa?

01:30:47.625 --> 01:30:48.458
Fadly.

01:30:50.291 --> 01:30:51.708
I love you.

01:30:54.500 --> 01:30:57.333
I'm willing to leave home
to fight for my love.

01:30:59.208 --> 01:31:00.750
Will you fight with me?

01:31:05.625 --> 01:31:06.750
Fadly.

01:31:08.666 --> 01:31:09.541
Nisa.

01:31:11.666 --> 01:31:12.833
To me,

01:31:14.541 --> 01:31:16.333
love isn't just about us.

01:31:19.250 --> 01:31:23.500
Our families have a love just as strong

01:31:24.208 --> 01:31:26.375
that deserves our fight.

01:31:29.666 --> 01:31:30.708
Go home.

01:31:32.958 --> 01:31:35.083
Let's move on with our lives.

01:31:37.291 --> 01:31:40.375
No one can leave
the past behind that fast.

01:31:40.458 --> 01:31:43.000
But sometimes, that's what we have to do

01:31:44.333 --> 01:31:46.666
for the people we love.

01:31:51.291 --> 01:31:52.375
I'm sorry.

01:31:55.541 --> 01:31:58.375
[bittersweet music]

01:32:08.041 --> 01:32:09.416
[sobbing]

01:32:38.208 --> 01:32:39.208
[clears throat]

01:33:15.375 --> 01:33:16.375
Do you

01:33:17.208 --> 01:33:19.708
enjoy reading as well?

01:33:21.750 --> 01:33:23.333
Mm…

01:33:23.416 --> 01:33:24.833
Not very often,

01:33:26.166 --> 01:33:29.500
but I'll read when I feel like it.

01:33:33.833 --> 01:33:35.041
As for me…

01:33:36.833 --> 01:33:38.083
Growing up,

01:33:38.916 --> 01:33:41.500
my parents always made me read.

01:33:43.083 --> 01:33:46.791
So reading became a daily habit.

01:33:53.000 --> 01:33:54.375
[hums]

01:33:54.458 --> 01:33:55.750
If

01:33:56.750 --> 01:34:02.333
you were forced to

01:34:03.958 --> 01:34:05.583
quit the music world

01:34:06.750 --> 01:34:08.583
to enter a new world,

01:34:11.125 --> 01:34:12.541
would you?

01:34:13.000 --> 01:34:13.833
[scoffs]

01:34:17.208 --> 01:34:19.541
That's a tough question.

01:34:23.125 --> 01:34:25.208
I don't know what to say.

01:34:26.458 --> 01:34:30.041
I truly love music.

01:34:32.916 --> 01:34:33.958
Mm.

01:34:35.333 --> 01:34:36.708
[sighs]

01:34:39.583 --> 01:34:41.750
-Rifa.
-Hm?

01:34:42.500 --> 01:34:43.750
I thought

01:34:45.166 --> 01:34:46.958
you wanted to meet

01:34:48.083 --> 01:34:51.541
to answer my proposal.

01:34:52.125 --> 01:34:55.333
[tender music]

01:34:57.875 --> 01:34:59.125
Sorry.

01:35:01.208 --> 01:35:03.416
I can't give you an answer right now.

01:35:11.791 --> 01:35:12.625
Fadly.

01:35:14.041 --> 01:35:14.875
Yeah?

01:35:16.250 --> 01:35:19.333
Are you proposing

01:35:20.916 --> 01:35:23.166
because you truly want to,

01:35:24.500 --> 01:35:26.208
or because of circumstances?

01:35:29.958 --> 01:35:31.041
[clears throat]

01:35:36.041 --> 01:35:37.000
Rifa.

01:35:38.125 --> 01:35:41.500
I understand what you're thinking,

01:35:42.458 --> 01:35:46.791
but it's really hard for me to explain

01:35:47.791 --> 01:35:52.708
that I do want to marry you
despite everything.

01:35:56.166 --> 01:35:57.916
How can I be sure

01:35:58.958 --> 01:36:01.500
that you've moved on from your ex?

01:36:15.250 --> 01:36:17.166
I have no explanation

01:36:18.041 --> 01:36:24.083
or proof that will be able to satisfy you…

01:36:27.000 --> 01:36:29.291
except for the chance that you give me.

01:36:32.416 --> 01:36:35.208
Who could have imagined that

01:36:36.291 --> 01:36:40.791
we'd be in this messy situation?

01:36:42.833 --> 01:36:45.958
Rifa, this is beyond my control.

01:36:48.833 --> 01:36:49.916
To be honest…

01:36:55.125 --> 01:36:57.416
I do have feelings for you.

01:37:00.333 --> 01:37:01.708
But also…

01:37:06.125 --> 01:37:08.458
I haven't seen you change.

01:37:12.125 --> 01:37:14.250
You're still the same coward as before.

01:37:17.833 --> 01:37:20.000
[Fatimah] I know this is hard for you.

01:37:21.333 --> 01:37:22.333
But

01:37:23.500 --> 01:37:26.458
things have come to this.

01:37:37.708 --> 01:37:40.208
Forgive me, and your Dad too.

01:37:45.458 --> 01:37:46.500
[Mustafa] Fadly.

01:37:47.833 --> 01:37:49.833
I think you should be with
Aunty Ina's daughter.

01:37:52.208 --> 01:37:53.041
Dear…

01:37:53.875 --> 01:37:56.375
[somber music]

01:37:57.583 --> 01:37:58.625
[phone dings]

01:38:03.333 --> 01:38:08.458
SORRY THINGS GOT SERIOUS EARLIER.
WE NEED TO HAVE A MATURE CONVERSATION.

01:38:08.541 --> 01:38:10.708
[children chattering]

01:38:12.583 --> 01:38:13.791
[Fadly] Apparently,

01:38:15.208 --> 01:38:17.291
life sucks when you're an adult.

01:38:20.083 --> 01:38:22.250
Being a kid was easier.

01:38:24.250 --> 01:38:25.750
No burdens.

01:38:27.458 --> 01:38:29.541
Just studying and having fun.

01:38:33.375 --> 01:38:36.541
I never thought I'd be dealing
with this problem.

01:38:38.500 --> 01:38:41.833
You can't stay a kid forever, you know?

01:38:43.791 --> 01:38:44.625
Sir.

01:38:47.916 --> 01:38:50.750
What if Rifa refuses to marry me?

01:38:54.375 --> 01:38:57.708
Live life to the fullest
of your capabilities.

01:38:58.625 --> 01:39:00.208
Create opportunities for yourself.

01:39:03.541 --> 01:39:06.000
You haven't met Rifa's parents, right?

01:39:08.500 --> 01:39:11.000
You said you don't want to be a coward.

01:39:11.833 --> 01:39:12.625
Right?

01:39:16.875 --> 01:39:19.375
There's a saying in Makassar,

01:39:20.333 --> 01:39:23.875
[speaking Makassarese]
"Kualleangi tallanga na toalia."

01:39:24.291 --> 01:39:28.208
"It would be better to sink
than to turn around."

01:39:29.000 --> 01:39:32.500
If God wills it, then it will happen.

01:39:35.500 --> 01:39:36.333
Right.

01:39:39.250 --> 01:39:40.208
Thanks, sir.

01:39:40.291 --> 01:39:41.458
You're welcome.

01:39:41.541 --> 01:39:44.166
[hopeful music]

01:40:00.416 --> 01:40:03.166
I came here to bring my son

01:40:04.041 --> 01:40:07.250
to propose to your daughter, Rifa.

01:40:13.291 --> 01:40:15.000
Well, sir.

01:40:15.083 --> 01:40:18.708
As her parents,
we'll leave the decision to her.

01:40:19.208 --> 01:40:20.625
How about you, dear?

01:40:20.708 --> 01:40:21.958
I think…

01:40:23.708 --> 01:40:25.000
it's up to Rifa.

01:40:25.833 --> 01:40:28.541
[sentimental music]

01:40:38.750 --> 01:40:40.125
I'm sorry.

01:40:42.583 --> 01:40:44.000
It's my fault

01:40:45.041 --> 01:40:47.791
the plan got ruined.

01:40:49.375 --> 01:40:51.500
It's all right.

01:40:51.583 --> 01:40:53.083
Stop worrying about it.

01:40:56.083 --> 01:40:57.791
I've made up my mind.

01:40:59.916 --> 01:41:01.083
I think

01:41:03.166 --> 01:41:06.416
I'll follow your choice, Mom, Dad.

01:41:10.041 --> 01:41:10.875
Mom.

01:41:12.083 --> 01:41:14.250
Let's visit Aunty Ina tomorrow.

01:41:16.833 --> 01:41:17.666
Fadly.

01:41:18.750 --> 01:41:21.125
Don't get married
just because of being pressured.

01:41:22.875 --> 01:41:24.333
It's not that.

01:41:26.250 --> 01:41:27.333
Anyway,

01:41:28.375 --> 01:41:31.875
you two just focus on
the wedding preparations.

01:41:32.250 --> 01:41:33.333
Are you sure?

01:41:33.416 --> 01:41:36.083
-I'm sure.
-[phone buzzing]

01:41:41.166 --> 01:41:42.125
Hello?

01:41:46.208 --> 01:41:47.875
[Rifa] Thank you, Fadly.

01:41:49.333 --> 01:41:51.166
[Rifa] I want to marry you.

01:41:53.458 --> 01:41:54.916
Praise God!

01:41:57.041 --> 01:41:59.958
[sniffles] Thank you, Rifa.

01:42:00.041 --> 01:42:02.833
["Celengan Rindu"
by Fiersa Besari playing]

01:42:03.625 --> 01:42:04.916
What?

01:42:05.000 --> 01:42:06.541
-It's Rifa.
-And what did she say?

01:42:06.625 --> 01:42:09.166
[Fadly] Thank God. Thank you, Rifa.

01:42:09.750 --> 01:42:10.833
Rifa.

01:42:15.750 --> 01:42:19.375
["Celengan Rindu" by Fiersa Besari
continues playing]

01:42:37.041 --> 01:42:38.791
[mouths] Hi.

01:42:40.791 --> 01:42:42.291
I can't believe this.

01:42:44.083 --> 01:42:46.416
You actually agreed to marry me.

01:42:47.875 --> 01:42:49.458
Because you've changed.

01:42:51.250 --> 01:42:53.083
You're no longer a coward.

01:43:01.166 --> 01:43:02.083
[groans]

01:43:02.708 --> 01:43:05.000
Took you long enough
to come to my parents' house.

01:43:06.083 --> 01:43:08.041
I'm tired of the marriage questions.

01:43:08.125 --> 01:43:09.166
[chuckles]

01:43:10.458 --> 01:43:13.833
After this, they'll ask you,
"When are you having kids?"

01:43:13.916 --> 01:43:16.416
-[Rifa hisses playfully]
-[Fadly groans, laughs]

01:43:17.166 --> 01:43:19.541
["Seberapa Pantas" by Sheila on 7 playing]

01:43:20.333 --> 01:43:22.041
Thank you.

01:43:23.958 --> 01:43:26.208
-[laughs]
-[exclaims] Congrats!

01:43:26.291 --> 01:43:28.333
You finally got married.

01:43:28.416 --> 01:43:30.166
Thanks to God.

01:43:30.250 --> 01:43:31.208
Thank you.

01:43:31.291 --> 01:43:32.166
Sir.

01:43:32.708 --> 01:43:33.666
Fadly.

01:43:34.125 --> 01:43:35.500
The universe came through.

01:43:36.000 --> 01:43:38.291
Fortunately, yes. Thank you.

01:43:40.041 --> 01:43:42.291
Rifa. Hold your breath.

01:43:42.375 --> 01:43:43.458
Why?

01:43:43.541 --> 01:43:44.583
Trust me.

01:43:45.333 --> 01:43:47.083
You're always late. [laughs]

01:43:48.416 --> 01:43:49.416
Sorry.

01:43:49.500 --> 01:43:50.541
Congratulations.

01:43:51.250 --> 01:43:52.208
-Thank you.
-Congrats, Fadly.

01:43:52.291 --> 01:43:53.041
[farts]

01:43:53.125 --> 01:43:55.625
Please pray that we're next.

01:43:55.708 --> 01:43:56.458
[farts]

01:43:56.541 --> 01:43:59.041
-Amen, "Fart Princess."
-[farts]

01:43:59.125 --> 01:44:00.666
[farts]

01:44:00.750 --> 01:44:01.833
Did you smell that?

01:44:03.166 --> 01:44:07.000
["Seberapa Pantas" by Sheila on 7
continues playing]

01:44:22.625 --> 01:44:26.666
One, two, three!

01:46:35.125 --> 01:46:37.833
[song ends]
